column13: Targets saggy, baggy and wrinkled skin, and ZAPS it back into shape!!!!
column14:
I've had the privilege of testing this Advanced Age-Defying Serum over the past month. This is the second Anaiti product from their skincare line that I've tried. This product is just as amazing as the last one. I really didn't think i could love another product as much as the Anaiti Wrinkle Smoothing Serum, but WOW did they create another perfect product geared directly at aging skin. This targets saggy, baggy and wrinkled skin, and ZAPS it back into its youthful, smooth and radiant form.

I have very dry skin, and because of that my skin seems to be aging more quickly. After I passed 30 my skin dried out even more and I knew I needed to find something to save my skin. I've tried so many products with little to no results. Then I was offered the chance to try this serum out and WOW!!! This is my skin's Hail Mary !!! It has revived my dull and lackluster complexion, and made it vibrant again. I saw results in about a week, and a huge improvement within the month. It absorbs quickly, is non-oily, and not sticky. It has a very light citrus smell, which fades quickly after application. I really like that unlike other serums this has a very thick lotion like texture and consistency.

My only complaint about it, is the packaging. I also own the Anaiti Wrinkle Smoothing Serum ( which i also highly recommend) The problem is the packaging is exactly the same, except for the product name on the front. I always have to do a double take to make sure I grabbed the right product. Though I must say, if the only thing I can complain about is the packaging Anaiti must be doing something very right, because i am very picky about my skincare.

So give this a try, I highly recommend it for those just starting to get a few skin imperfections or those with deep set wrinkles. If your skin has lost it's pizzazz, this will more than likely give you some of that back. You really can't go wrong, they even offer a 100% money back guarantee. So pick some up today.
- I received this product free for testing purposes, but all opinions are my own.

column13: A solid oil with a great scent
column14:
I originally purchased the beard balm from Honest Amish, and while I liked the scent and its conditioning power, it was just too heavy to really work into my beard. It did work well for my mustache, which isn't very filled in nor as coarse/curly hair as my beard.
The classic beard oil smells exactly like the regular balm...perfect! Its not pine-y or forest-y, nor is it musky or 'fresh'...I guess I'd call it a manly 'spice' scent that is not overpowering.
Its much thinner than a different brand I'd been using, much closer to that of pure jojoba oil (which I also use on the beard). This makes it a lot easier to apply, especially if the beard isn't damp (it's hard to keep short beard damp after all).
The dropper could be a little better constructed, but its not problematic either...just my preference.
I have fairly sensitive skin, and haven't had issues with any irritation nor pimple formation.

column6: Hibiclens Antimicrobial Skin Liquid Soap
column13: My skin would start peeling in a matter of days and flake (to the point where I could wipe my face with my hands and it would be
column14:
I use it to wash my face now. I used to get break outs all the time, and facial cleansers would just dry it out. My skin would start peeling in a matter of days and flake (to the point where I could wipe my face with my hands and it would be like snowing :( ) beneath all the peeling skin, I would have a lot of break outs. So it was a very difficult skin type to figure out what I needed because I have oily skin that breaks out a lot, but dries out and starts peeling, so I normally had to choose between the two extremes, and makeup would draw more attention to my peeling skin.

I actually found out that rubbing this on my face with my fingertips and following it up with warm water worked better than anything I've ever used and any facial. It didn't dry out my skin, but it kept fighting the bacteria that caused my face to break out so I could wear makeup and go about my day with no problem.

The difference was seriously over night. Even makeup goes on my face very smoothly and cleanly, so I have a flawless complexion. Basically it lets the oils go back in to my skin so it doesn't peel, but it keeps my oily skin from getting infected, resulting in very soft and gentle complexion. Miracle product.

column6: TRESemm√© Expert Selection Flexi Bounce Mousse, Youth Boost 8.1 oz
column14:
If you use a round brush to blow dry your hair, you know about "grab". You need to be able to have your hair hold on the brush long enough to pick up a curl and then be able to release without getting stuck. Without product on it, my hair just slides off the brush (unless I keep twirling it like a motorized spaghetti fork). Some spray gels give a good amount of traction but then I have to wrestle to get the brush loose and drag half the curl back out in the process.

This Mousse did an excellent job of giving just the right amount of grab on the brush without giving any problems on the release. In fact, it does the best of any product I've tried in that respect. My hair was left soft and shiny without any stiffness. I think this product is best for a soft hairstyle, something that moves and blows with the wind. If you need a firmer hold or some stiffness to create your style, you'll need to add some spray or gel after you blow dry because the mousse alone won't set or hold a style.

Other than that, the dispenser is easy to use and the scent is subtle yet pleasant. Recommended amount is "2-3 applications". I guess they didn't feel that "blob" or "glob" was appropriate language for product labeling!

column6: Nizoral Anti-Dandruff Shampoo
column13: Nizoral is a Miracle Anti-Dandruff Shampoo!!
column14:
After wasting hundreds of dollars on anti-dandruff products. I was desperate. My hair was flaky, itchy, stinky, and falling out!! It wasn't until I told my sister about the problems I was having that I found out about Nizoral. She told me that when her baby girl had really bad cradle cap her doctor suggested that she use Nizoral and Hydro cortisone to stop the itch. On hearing this, I ordered Nizoral right a way. After the first use, I could see and feel a difference. Usually, after washing my hair, my head would still be itchy and it would start getting flaky after a few days. After, using Nizoral, I went a whole week without washing my hair and I had only a few flakes!!! I have been using Nizoral for about a month now and my hair is no longer falling out. It is no longer itchy and it only gets somewhat flaky after going about a week without washing it.Thus, I would suggest this to anyone who really wants to put an end to their dandruff!!!

Thank you Johnson & Johnson for creating such a wonderful anti-dandruff shampoo. Now, I just have to find a good product that will grow my hair back :(.

Anyway, long story short I tried Remington and I am very happy. Shaves as well as the Norelco and for a fraction of the price. I like the indicator telling me how many minutes of charge I have left. It is a little noisier than the Norelcos. Happy with the purchase, I have had it for a little over a year now.

column6: FRENCH TWIST HAIR COMB 9 THOOTH IT DELUXE
column14: Combs like these are difficult to find and when you do find them they are overpriced. The key, as someone else mentioned, is the number of teeth. These are a little thinner than comparable products but that's part of the reason I like them. I have thick, heavy, long hair and they hold my hair up well and yet are lightweight enough that I can lean my head back against the car headrest, couch, or bed and don't feel any poking or head twisting as I do with other comb products and hair claws. Worth the wait and will order more. At this price point I can order quite a few in case of breakage.

column6: Proactiv 3 Step Acne Treatment System (60 Day)
column13: MEDIOCRITY IS UNACCEPTABLE FOR THE PRICE!!!!
column14: Overpriced for bottle sizes.  Ordered off TV and very disappointed with the results after using the product! This product is mediocre at best, albeit I do not have severe acne.  However, as an adult, I'm finding using regular soap is drying out my skin and leaving white dry, flaky, patches all over my face that severely itch and begin to peel (not to mention, left me with an uneven skin complexion)!  So I began trying different methods.  I found better results using an oil-free 2% salicylic acid acne wash (I currently use the Walgreen's brand--which costs about $6.00) works beyond great!  After washing my face with this wash, I use amLactin lotion which contains 12% lactic acid ( can get a 2 oz. bottle on Amazon for $2.99) otherwise; it can get pricey. I LOVE the results.  Only after a couple of uses I noticed a difference.  No more itching, peeling, discoloration of my skin, or blackheads on my nose.  This combination works great for me!

column13: This does the job fine of curling your lashes
column14: This does the job fine of curling your lashes.  However, I would not recommend this particular eyelash curler if you have bad arthritis in your hands. The handle is in an automatic expanded position and you have to lightly squeeze it in to curl your lashes.

column6: Beauty by Earth Natural SPF Sunscreen - All Natural, Mineral & Organic Ingredients - Non-Nano Zinc, Non-Toxic for Whole Family and Reef Safe - Made in the USA
column13: but I was very disappointed in the product
column14: I ordered this sunscreen based on the reviews I read, but I was very disappointed in the product. I ordered this due to my son (who has eczema) recently developed an allergic reaction to Banana Boat and Water Babies sunscreens. I bought it also due to it being "Natural and Reef Safe." I was hoping to use it in Hawaii because of that. However, it was hard to spread on his body. It dispensed well, but it was very hard to rub into the skin. It left white streaks everywhere the product was applied. This caused him to not be protected in those areas as his body was tanned in the areas adjacent to the white streaks. I was very disappointed in the product so I returned it. The only thing I liked about it was that it stated it was "reef safe."

column13: The Search is over my bearded brethern!
column14: After giving Honest Amish Heavy Duty Beard Balm a long and drawn out testing stage, I feel compelled to share my experience with the rest of the beard nation! I was your typical everyday working man with a wild beard that could not be tamed. I tried every fancy fly by night brand looking to jump on the new beard fad band wagon and finally went to something good ole fashioned and hand made with natural ingredients. I start my day with dampening my beard and the applying the balm. Inside my tin the balm had separated but it became a relaxing ritual to slowly melt it all down in the palm of my hand (if you so choose you can melt the balm in a pan with warm water but I didn't find this necessary). At night if I choose to wash my beard, I use old fashioned pine tar soap for that, I will apply the beard oil the Honest Amish also makes. My lesson has been learned, My beard is soft and manageable and has just the slightest hint of a pleasant licorice smell that will disappear after a short time. Do yourself a favor and don't buy the fancy cans with crazy designs and logos, get this and have a beard that you and that significant other will enjoy

column14:

I've been using the French Red Konjac sponge for several months now, and I could tell within the first week that it was working. I'm still stunned both by the difference in my skin and by the thought of how much I've needlessly spent on skin care products over the years. I was looking at sonic skin care cleaners when I happened upon this link, I am SO happy/elated/ecstatic that I did.
The Konjac sponge is incredibly easy to use. The first time it needs to soak in warm water, then the water needs to be pressed out of it between your hands, then you're ready to go. (Never wring out the sponge, it'll wear it out quicker. There are very easy to follow instructions included). Then you wash your face with the sponge. (If it makes it easier, pretend there's a cleanser on the sponge, so it won't seem so weird NOT using a cleanser on your face). :)

column6: ULTIMATE Vitamin C Serum 22% Advanced Proprietary Blend Vitamin C E Ferulic + 11% Hyaluronic + 1% E + 1% Ferulic Acid
column13: Newer Dispenser Destroyed a Fantastic Product
column14: Okay, this is an amazing product.  It has done more for my 50-year-old sun-damaged skin than anything I've ever tried previously.  Here's the problem: the packaging is a nightmare.  The serum used to come in a bottle with a screw-on eye-dropper cap.  You had precise control over how much you dispensed each time.  Now it comes with a pump - the worst possible pump-style for this type of product.  I absolutely promise you that there is no way to avoid wasting a good amount of product every time you use it.  The pump points straight out at a 90-degree angle from the bottle (strike one - what's the point of that??  It's a liquid - it's just going to drip off of whatever it hits unless the target is horizontal) and it has a very stiff "action," meaning that you have to press the pump hard to get it to depress.  This is strike two because it means you have little or no control over how fast the product comes out.  If you don't tilt the bottle so it shoots diagonally into your hand, the serum will shoot (and I literally mean shoot) straight out from the bottle and fly across your bathroom.  Even when it's tilted to point toward your hand, the high-pressure pump causes it to squirt so hard that some of it usually ricochet's off your hand and onto the floor (or mirror, or sink, or...).  Even if tilting it prevented all product loss (it doesn't), it would still be a bad design because you wouldn't be able to get anything out of the bottle at a tilt after using 2/3 or 3/4 of the bottle - you'd have to hold it upright so the tube inside would still be in contact with the product, otherwise it wouldn't pump out anything except air.  It's so frustrating because it takes all control away from you and causes you to have to buy the product more often since so much gets wasted just trying to dispense it.  I initially thought the company changed to a pump so the consumer would not have to unscrew the cap and expose the serum to germs, but the terrible design almost makes it seem as if it was planned to act this way on purpose so we would be forced to buy more product more often.  I realize that's highly unlikely, but as I said before, it's ridiculously frustrating.  I've bought a few bottles since the change, just to see if maybe the first bottle or two with the pumps came from a bad batch, but they're all like this.  I hate to change products, but it makes no sense to waste so much of this serum.  I'm sad to say that I'll now be looking elsewhere.  There are many Vitamin C Serum makers that sell their products on Amazon - I'm sure to find something similar.  I wish I'd saved an old bottle.  I would just keep reusing it by pouring out the newer bottles into the old one so I could keep using the dropper (what a pain).  5 stars for the serum, 0 stars for the packaging.em as if it was planned to act this way on purpose so we would be forced to buy more product more often.  I realize that's highly unlikely, but as I said before, it's ridiculously frustrating.  I've bought a few bottles since the change, just to see if maybe the first bottle or two with the pumps came from a bad batch, but they're all like this. column6: Philips Norelco Rq12+ Replacement Head For Series 8000 (Sensotouch 3D) And Arcitec
column13: I didn't want to believe that Norelco had ruined my great SensorTouch 3D 1250x shaver
column14:
After reading so many negative reviews about the RQ12+ replacement shaver head, and a handful of positive reviews, I didn't want to believe that Norelco had ruined my great SensorTouch 3D 1250x shaver, wiped out the $220 investment I made 3 years ago and forced me into the arms of a competitor.

But they did.

I should mention that I always shave in the shower and use shaving foam. My beard is relatively light and grows every which-way, so regardless of the shaver it takes several passes to get a close shave. About 10 years ago or so I tried several different electric shaver models, including one Norelco, and they all failed in the shower due to water leakage. And they didn't shave very close. I spent the next decade shelling out big bucks for the various Gillette Fusion upgrades, including the powered models, and ever-more expensive blades. Got a close shave but got nicked a lot, too.

Finally, I found the Norelco SensorTouch 3D 1250x. What a great razor! It worked flawlessly in the shower -- water simply can't get inside the mechanism. The shave was nearly as close as the Fusion blades. And the cleaning system was excellent. I felt that I'd finally found the answer.

I don't shave every day, so the first head lasted 18 months. I replaced it with another RQ12/52 and the shave continued to be excellent. 18 months later, I couldn't buy the RQ12/52 anymore, except at outrageous prices -- some greater than what I paid for the 1250x shaver and cleaning system. I read the RQ12+ reviews with some trepidation, but there were enough positive reviews to give the new head a shot

The first time I used the RQ12+, I thought it was better than the negative reviews indicated. But the more I shaved with the RQ12+ them more I noticed that the shaver was missing a lot of area on each pass and it was taking more and more passes to get a close shave. Some specifics: The RQ12+ head couldn't deal with the heaviest part of my beard, theupper lip and chin. The shave was never close and I couldn't get all the way to the nostrils. Didn't have either problem with the RQ12/52. Also, I frequently got an ingrown hair near the corner of my upper lip. It was in nearly the same spot every time. Had to pull it out with tweezers. I guess the hair wants to flop over and grow down, and the RQ12+ head couldn't lift it up.

I decided to put up with this for at least a month to make sure it wasn't just a case of my beard and shaving style needing to adjust to the new heads. In fact, I did better than that -- I used the RQ12+ for three months. But the shave never improved and I finally gave up. It was hard to flush $220 down the drain, but I'd had enough. I did a bunch of research and bought the Braun Series 7 799CC-6WD CC4 Wet & Dry Shaver:

http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00BWRLJ6O?psc=1&redirect=true&ref_=oh_aui_detailpage_o02_s00

I couldn't be more pleased with the Braun 799CC. The shave is actually closer than the Norelco 1250x with the RQ12/52 head. Smooth as a straight razor, but without the nicks. I can go more days without shaving than I could before. What really surprises me is how even the shave is. My beard never grew back so evenly with the Norelco. The Braun 799CC works great in the shower and the cleaning/charging system is better than the Norelco.

So, even though I'm disappointed and angry at having my investment wiped out, I'm glad to have found a better shaver.

Very bad call, Norelco.

column6: Mirage - Acne Scar and Enlarged Pore Filler and Concealer
column13: Very impressed! Highly recommend for deep scars
column14:
I have a huge (not exaggerating) ice pick scar on the front of my nose that was totally impossible to camouflage. After watching the Youtube video on how to apply it, it worked like nothing I have ever seen! It is very moist and fills the "hole", so I pat it in and then wipe the excess away. It dries pretty slowly so I do this a few times while I am getting ready for work, but if I am in a hurry I use a hair dryer. It dries clear but blends into my skin tone as if it wasn't there, and all you see is a smooth surface (like dried glue). I dab a tiny bit of concealer or a little powder on it before I leave and it stays in place all day.
When I take my makeup off at night, sometimes I have to remove the filler with tweezers because it is so embedded into my scar, but it is soft and easy to do. It has the consistency of gum or putty, and does not hurt to remove.
I was a little bit apprehensive about buying such an expensive concealer, and admit I haven't tried any of the other products out there to compare, but this really does the job. I am a regular Amazon customer, and was not asked (or otherwise coerced) into writing this review- I simply want to share my experience so others won't be discouraged by the price. It is worth it!

column6: For Pro Ultrasonic Diffuser, Savasana
column14:
Before testing out the SAVASANA ULTRASONIC AROMA DIFFUSER, I had never used a diffuser before. Therefore, I have nothing I can compare this device to. In short, I found the SAVASANA ULTRASONIC AROMA DIFFUSER really easy to use and enjoyed the different fragrances this puppy filled the air with.

This diffuser is plastic, but it has a wooden finish that gives it an appearance of being more exotic. If you have it sitting around and don't tell anyone, they will think it's real wood until they touch it. There's a band around the middle of this thing that changes color if you want it to. The power outlet is on the back with two buttons. The right button controls the rate of mist and the left button controls the color of the band (you can change it to a specific color, turn on the cascade effect, or turn it off).

When first using this device, I was surprised at how much water it used. It comes equipped with a little cup to fill up the basin, but you can just use an ordinary glass if you want. The basin contains about a pint of water. After filling, you add a few drops of oil and then the device is ready to fill the air with pleasant aromas. It will run for about 3-4 hours before misting out.

The bottom of the device has four little feet with rubber tips that help keep it stable. Also, it should be noted that this device doesn't use any heat. That's a nice thing to know because a person can feel safe using this in the bedroom or in a living quarters and not have to worry about it overheating.

Overall, I found the SAVASANA ULTRASONIC AROMA DIFFUSER very pleasant to use. In all honesty, it didn't do much for me personally, but it did make my bedroom smell really nice for a while.

I was provided a sample of this item from the manufacturer for examination and possible review.

column6: Vidal Sassoon Pro Series Hair Color 1 Deep Black 1 Kit
column13: Enjoyed the hints of purple but really didn't last long
column14:
I was given the chance to try this product for free by Vidal Sassoon and by being a member of Bzz Agent. I was really excited when I was invited to try the product because I had wanted to colour my hair purple for a really long time but I couldn't find a colour I really liked. The colour on the box was perfect and despite my dark brown roots, the "simulated" pictures on the box looked like the colour would come out vibrant enough on my dark hair as well. I had read reviews that one box was insufficient and that the dye was runny. I found that the dye was actually perfectly creamy. It was runny enough to get through my hair properly but creamy enough to stay on my hair without leaking everywhere. I also found that unlike other colouring products, very little product leaked/fell on the floor since the consistency of the product was good. Also, unlike every other colouring products I've tried, this one barely smelled like ammonia and instead had a floral scent so that was nice.

My hair is about medium length and goes a little lower than my shoulders. My hair is also pretty thick. One bottle was enough to colour my whole head. After I was done applying colour to every strand, I actually still had leftover product to spread over areas that seemed drier. Initially, after rinsing (no shampoo, as per the instructions) and drying my hair, it looked really dark. My hair is naturally very dark brown but the dye made my hair noticeably darker. I looked in all sorts of different lights and I could only see subtle hints of purple. Definitely not what I expected. After a few washes, however, the colour got brighter and the purple showed a little more (but only in the sunlight). The colour however had more hints of red than purple. The colour also became a lot more uneven after only 3 washes. My hair had been coloured before so the bottom half of it was a lighter brown, sort of copper. Although the dye initially coloured my hair evenly, once the dye started fading the discoloured‚Äã part of my hair showed again. Finally, it's been 4 weeks since I coloured my hair and the colour is pretty much all gone, with only little hints of pink.

It was fun while it lasted but I probably wouldn't buy it again. The photo attached is from the second week when the colour started fading and the purple started showing more but so did my previously discolored hair.

column6: ULTIMATE OCEAN Mineral Organic Facial Cleanser Offers High-End Spa Quality Oceanic Minerals Will Nourish Dry Skin & Damaged Skin, Diminish Discoloration & Leave your Skin Clean, Healthy, & Youthful!
column14:
I have been using 4 of the Azure Naturals products so I am going to review in order of recommended use.

The seaweed hydration mask is really cool. It is not clay based so it doesn't get super stiff like some of the masks I have used in the past. The hardening of the masks really bugs me as I am not a big fan of putting things on my face, but also know I need to take better care of my skin. I like this mask because it sort of feels like your skin is tightening but then it can be rinsed off. Like other masks, you use a warm towel to remove it. It is pretty easy to remove it because of the lack of hardening to the face. A lot less messy! My skin feels really refreshed after using it so that is a huge plus!! It smells sort of aloe-y and you don't need a whole ton of the product to get a good spread. It states that it can be used on the neck and whole body as well. I have major sensory issues so I haven't attempted beyond my face :-D but I imagine your skin would feel very refreshing after rinsing it off!

After the mask you can use the cleanser. Sometimes I have skipped this step as my skin already feels pretty good after the mask. The cleanser is a sort of gel and comes out in a pump bottle. It has a sort of smell like a light flower. It dries on your face nicely but if you have any sort of sensory issues, this may be the one that takes the longest to get used to. I only need one pump, lather it with a bit of warm water, and it seems to be enough to cover the face with a frothy thin layer. After you rinse and your face dries it feels nice and seems to leave a tightening feeling on the skin.

The toner feels really good on the face! It comes in a spray bottle and should be used after washing your face and if you have the complex cleanser you can use it after that. It comes out as a beautiful mist that sprayed at a distance, covers my entire face. But I use two sprays just because it feels pretty darn refreshing. It dries really quickly so if you are using the hydration creme, you only need to wait a few seconds to put it on. It smells really good too!

After the toner, and as the final step in the complete series, you use the creme. I love the creme and this is probably my favorite of the four. After all of the work on your skin and face, the creme feels so incredible and refreshing. Again, you don't need a whole lot of it to feel like you have covered your face. It has a really good smell, similar to the mask but not too strong. This is the product that seems to pull it all together for me. When I put it on, it feels like I am sort of giving my skin a protective moist layer to keep all of the good stuff on long enough for my skin to absorb the ingredients. It dries nice and smooth and doesn't feel oily afterwords. I give it some time to do it's job while I change or eat breakfast and then I come back to put some powder makeup on over it.

These products are organic and show you right on the front of the bottle exactly what you are getting, organic aloe, irish moss, shea butter, rosehip, tea tree oil, sprirulina, and sea kelp. Can't get more natural than that! I have all 4 products and using them all together feels even better so if possible, I'd recommend getting one of their toners, cleansers, cremes, and masks.

column6: Schick Quattro For Women Razor
column13: Probably not manufacture recommendations, but when it works this well why fix what's not broken?
column14: I have no idea what you ladies are doing to shave where this razor doesnt shave legs well?  I share mine with my two teen daughters, probably not recommended, but we do anyway.  We each shave every other day, we keep the blade clean and dry when not in use and use just regular soap (Zest) foamy on our legs while we shower. All this and I change the razor every couple months. I say we go through a four blade package once a year. We have very smooth legs, no stubble or razor burn, and I only change the blade that often for sanitation. We have used this and other Shick razors exclusively for nearly 10 years and I have owned maybe 5 or 6 handles that whole time. It lasts forever and for the price of anything else, even disposables that used to nick me or slice my ankles, knees, etc everytime I feel this is nearly free for how much it costs vs. the flawless use we have for 3 people over such an extended period of time.  Nothing is made like this anymore. Very happy with this product.

column6: Le Edge Full Body Exfoliator - Blue
column14:
EXFOLIATE! EXFOLIATE! I don't think alot of people understand how important and simple it is to exfoliate from head to toe. Exfoliation allows skin to breathe, rejuvenate, new cells to emerge, improves blood circulation etc .I've tried the good ole mesh pouf, wash rag, body brush, Moroccan glove (which works well btw paired with Moroccan black soap, for a deep all over scrub & smoothness!) and others.
I live in the Caribbean so this environment can leave you a a bit sticky and clammy more than usual so this works great. I don't have sensitive skin so I can glide/scrape this baby anytime i am in the shower. After I lather up and rinse off, I use the blade and I scrape the day's gunk off. Yup I do see those dead skin rolls and this climate requires me to lotion up well so that also adds to to the gunk. Now I use it about 2-3 times a week, especially if there has been some tanning under our hot sun.
I even got a 2nd one for my husband to use on his face. It helps get his black/white heads off (yeah i was surprised he asked for one lol). Great buy! Love it! Does the job!

I mean my skin is baby soft. I also see an ever so slight texture change. I can tell right now that over time this is going to work out very well.

Nothing to think about. Buy it and see if it works for you. Highest Possible Recommendation.

column6: Braun Series
column13: I've had NO issues that others have had, it works perfectly for me on my Braun 8985, smooth no-snag shave like it should be.
column14:
I too had read many of the other reviews here that say how horrible this shaver replacement is, and I too was worried just like you probably are. I put off ordering one since I didn't want a piece of junk, I wanted a real replacement. I haven't replaced my foil and cutter in about 4 yrs (and they recommend doing it every 1.5yrs) and it was getting to where I really really needed to, even at the risk of getting what many here are calling a junk replacement. Well, since I couldn't find any others, I ordered the "Series 5, 51S" for about $30. When it came I noticed the foil head had even-sized small holes throughout, whereas the last replacement I bought (~4 yrs ago) had more of a honeycomb look to the holes. 'Oh boy' I thought, 'Maybe this will be a bad thing like so many others have said'.

Nope, not a bad thing at all! It works perfectly! It is so smooth, so much quieter than what my other cutter/foil had become, it's almost as if it's a new razor altogether. I have a thick heavy beard, similar to Homer Simpson it seems I have a 5 'oclock shadow an hour after I shave. I had a 3 day beard when this arrived and I started first on my neck. It plowed through like it was a gas-powered lawnmower. I went on to my face, same thing. Beautiful! It really made it quite clear how bad my other cutter had become. Instead of 5 or 6 litle passes over the same spots, this one took care of the stubble in 1-2 passes.

I use a Braun 8985, BEFORE it was branded "360 Complete", or Syncro, or any of that. Mine has no LCD display on it, just the plain Braun 8985 from, if memory serves correctly, the early 2000s...not sure if this makes a difference in fit or performance. The attached pic is exactly what mine looks like, but it's a stock image for reference. This foil cutter fits it perfectly, and works flawlessly. Honestly, I realize this sounds cliche, but I couldn't be happier. If memory serves me correctly, I paid double this for replacements in the past.

Regarding the many negative reviews of this Series 5 replacement, perhaps other sellers are selling factory seconds, or perhaps there's some slight fit problems with the newer models of the 8900 series such as Activator and 360, I don't know. But the one I got from this seller, "EveryDay-Shop"
@ http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B001VEK1IU?psc=1&redirect=true&ref_=od_aui_detailpages00
was the real deal.

Good luck and I hope this is helpful.

column6: Sweet Almond Oil for Skin, Hair and Face - Large 16oz - WITH PUMP + FREE Recipe eBook! - All Natural Sensual Massage Oil - Use with Essential Oils and Aromatherapy as a Carrier and Base oil
column14:
I love this sweet almond oil! It comes with a pump cap and a squirt cap, which is pretty convenient. It's almost completely scent-free, which is awesome if you're like me and hate using scented oils in your hair (I love the smell of my shampoo too much, I hate covering it up!). For the body, I like a little scent, and it makes a lovely carrier for essential oils. I add a bit of my favorite EO of the moment, (Plant Therapy's Tranquil Synergy) and I massage over damp skin - and now my skin is silky-smooth :). I find that it is best to use this, and any carrier oil over damp skin, or after a spritz of floral water/hydrosol. The almond oil really locks in the moisture, and sinks into the skin leaving you smooth and hydrated, and sweetly scented, if you added some EO. Best of all? It's all natural! A HUGE plus for me, since I've been switching over to all-natural products, as of late :).
Another thing this product is great for is oil-cleansing. Massage a bit, with or without essential oils (lavender and tea tree is a good place to start!) into the face. Run hot water over a washcloth, and wring it out. Lay it over your face, and the steam should remove any excess oil. Your skin is left clean and silky smooth! Give this a try, and you may give up on soaps and commercial cleansers for good!

Definitely recommend this product!!

column6: Alberto VO5 Shine, Glow & Go Beauty Oil 5.9 fl oz.
column13: Primarily a body oil; amazing for exfoliating
column14:
This is a light, unscented blend of non-comedogenic oils, and I keep finding new uses for it.

A light spritz on my legs before shaving and I can skip soap or shaving gel. The razor just glides and I get a close, non-irritating shave.

A very light spritz on my hair before towel drying, and it combs like a dream. Light is the key here; a minuscule amount goes a long way. Any more than that and it'll be greasy.

I use this oil once a month for an oil cleanse on my skin; after washing, I massage some of this into my problem areas like t-zone and anywhere I get clogged pores. After about 10 minutes of massage, I lay a hot washcloth over my face. When it cools, I do it again, and then use the cloth to wipe away any remaining gunk and oil. Clean pores!

Best of all I use this together with a strigil like the Le Edge Full Body Exfoliator that I also found on Amazon. In the shower or bath I spritz some of this oil anywhere I have dry skin, KP bumps, blocked follicles, etc., rub it in, wait a minute or two and then gently scrape away layers of dead skin. What's left is fresh, smooth and glowing.

column13: Sock-eez helps, but only a little bit
column14:
The Sock-eez does help some with support hose removal, but not in the way shown in the videos. The first step of getting the leading edge to the floor goes smoothly. Twisting the Sock-eez as you do that also goes quite easily. When you reach that point, you are supposed to point your toe down and slide your heel up the ramp. That does not go well at all. One or both of two things happen ‚Äî the Sock-eez starts to bend and/or your heel slips sideways off the incline.

The lady who demos this (wife of the designer) is able to point her foot almost in line with her leg ‚Äî almost like a ballerina. For those of us who can't, I believe this greatly increases the difficulty of the final removal step. If they really wanted to sell this product, they would use a model who has real difficulty using this tool and coach him/her on what to do differently. Whether such coaching would be effective is not certain.

column14: I placed my order for Acetyl Organics' Argireline Botox Anti-Aging Serum on July 22, 2015 and received my shipment well in advance of the projected estimated delivery period. It arrived in good condition and I began using the product as directed, twice daily for what has been about two weeks now. The serum goes on well, is not the least bit oily, and penetrates the skin almost immediately. It may be premature to make a judgement of its effectiveness on my wrinkles yet, but so far, I really have not seen any significant change. I am a 56 year old female, already using Vitamin C and hyaluronic acid so was anxious to determine if the argireline would make any difference. My only complaint is that the eye dropper style bottle seems to leak easily and I lost some of the contents when it was placed on its side during air travel. I will continue to use the product in lieu of my previous regime because it does include all the ingredients I was previously using plus Vitamin A and the argireline that have been suggested to be included in an anti-aging treatment.

I keep it in the car for easy access when I arrive at the office and find that I missed a section while shaving with a disposable razor or just need a quick touchup before an evening meeting.  You could easily buy four of these for the price of one rechargeable rotary unit.

column6: Cliradex Natural Eyelid, Eyelash, and Facial Cleansing Towelettes, Box of 24
column13: 100% effective; it's a MIRACLE. Here's my daily regimen
column14:
These wipes really work. I had suffered from dry eye in my left eye that left me with blurry vision and eye discomfort for the past three years. I use my eyes very hard every day, I'm on the computer 8-12 hours (I'm a 58 year old woman with rosacea). I am an artist, and need crisp vision to do my work. Needless to say this dry eye issue was much more than a distraction, it affected my quality of life. I tried all sorts of solutions, some of which I still use in my daily eye care regimen. Over the years, my ophthalmologist prescribed Azasite, which would help for a short time but then the symptoms would return.

I poked around on the internet and stumbled across these wipes, and thought I would give it a try. Well, I noticed an improvement on the first day, and it's been about 6 weeks now and my vision is the most stable it has been in a long time. I no longer have eye discomfort or pain during the day or night. My left eye feels HEALTHY in a way it has not felt in a LONG time. The key was learning how often to use the wipe, how much of it to leave on the lids, and how long. At least for me, more is not better. I learned that too much Cliradex sitting on my lids will gum up the meibomian glands on the eyelids (where the oil comes out). That's the last thing I wanted to happen, the whole point of using Cliradex is to kill my demodex mites that are causing dysfunction in the glands. I don't wash off the Cliradex at night, but I do give my eyes a good cleansing in the morning to remove it, first with an OcuSoft scrub, then with a clean washcloth (no soap). I only use Cliradex once a day at night. Here's my daily regimen, learned through trial and error. Hopefully this will help you too:

BEFORE BED:
--Wash your face with a gentle fragrance-free cleanser.
--Heat a Thermalon Dry Eye Compress in a microwave for 20 seconds, lay on your back on the bed with the compress on both eyes for five minutes.
--Then gently massage both eyelids with your index finger, using a back and forth motion with your eyes closed, not pressing too hard. Look up while doing this.
--Get one packet of Cliradex wipes, cut it in half with a clean scissors (you can feel where the wipe is in the packet). Depending on how you cut it, you can get three pieces to use over three days. Put the extras in a plastic ziplock.
--If doing this for the first time, sit down to apply the wipe since it will sting for about two minutes. Have a piece of paper nearby that you can fan your face with so it dries quicker, once it dries it will stop stinging. Take the wipe and close your eyes (don't squeeze them, just close them like you're sleeping). With your index finger, wipe back and forth with three motions (left, right, left) and then do the other eye, then use the wipe on your eyebrows, nose and cheeks. Wait until the stinging stops to open your eyes.
--Do not use more than three wipe motions on each eye. If you put too much of the Cliradex on your lids, it can plug up your meibomian glands on your eyelids (where the oil comes out).
--Do not wash off the Cliradex. Leave it on all night.

DURING SLEEP
--Wear EyeSeals Thermoplastic Eye Shield to trap moisture around your eyes.

MORNING
--Wash your face with a gentle fragrance-free cleanser.
--Wash your eyes with an Ocusoft Scrub wipe (don't get the generic, it doesn't work as well). You can also cut these in half. Use the wipe with your eyes closed, and leave the solution on your eyes for 30 seconds. This will help get the Cliradex solution off your eyelids so your oil glands can run freely.
--Wash eyes with warm water.
--Heat a Thermalon Dry Eye Compress in a microwave for 20 seconds, lay on your back on the bed with the compress on both eyes for five minutes.
--Then gently massage both eyelids with your index finger, using a back and forth motion with your eyes closed, not pressing too hard. Look up while doing this.
--(optional) Put Systane Preservative-Free Vial drops in your eyes.
--Throughout the day, as needed, run a paper towel under cold tap water and gently wipe your lids with your eyes closed.

I saw my ophthalmologist recently and he was flabbergasted at how good my eyelashes looked. He said he had never seen signs of mites, and he was quite surprised that this product worked for me. It really made him think. He said he had Cliradex samples in his office but never gave them out because no came into his office with the kind of eyelash symptoms he was looking for. Which goes to show that someone can be having demodex issues without it being visibly apparent.r towel under cold tap water and gently wipe your lids with your eyes closed. column6: Philips Sonicare 2 Series Plaque Control Rechargeable Toothbrush
column13: great toothbrush, not too loud and relatively stable despite comments from some reviewers
column14:
i spent a lot of time looking at reviews for the philips sonicare products. i had an oral b electric toothbrush that i was very happy with, but my dentist recommended the sonicare so i decided to give it a try. this is the simplest (and cheapest) of the sonicare line. many of the review suggested that the gadgets on the more expensive sonicare products (3 series, healthy white, diamond care, flexcare, etc) were not really helpful (timers, pressure sensors, variable settings, etc.) and i agree. i just wanted a toothbrush that would work and didn't want too many buttons to deal with or complexities that could break.

i have had the sonicare 2 series for a month now and i'm very happy with it. some reviewers complained about the noise--it is not any louder than my oral b electric toothbrush and the noise doesn't bother me. it is noticeable, but even my guests don't find it annoying. some reviewers also mention that the stand isn't very stable. this is true, but the charge lasts 2-3 weeks so i only put it on the stand when the battery is dead. the rest of the time the toothbrush can stand on the counter alone and it is very stable by itself since the bottom is very flat. overall, a great toothbrush and a great value at this price (the same brush at target was almost double the price).

column14: I found this toothpaste last year at our local Wegman's. My kids loved it! My son has  a sensory disorder where certain tastes, textures, smells can send him gagging from the room , and he's 20! It's better than when he was little but still challenging because he cannot handle any minty toothpastes. My problem is that I've developed a sensitivity to minty toothpaste which causes blisters in my mouth. My dentist said they are chemical burns and for people with lots of allergies (like me) that this is pretty common. You can imagine my frustration, then, when our local store stopped carrying this toothpaste. Yeah, there's kiddie toothpaste but that is too sweet, and any "natural" stuff is off limits because I'm allergic to so many of those ingredients. I am so very grateful that I found this toothpaste on Amazon. I am not exaggerating when I say that I would cry if the company stopped making this. I really don't want to use baking soda like my doctor said I might have to use. This flavor is not for everybody, that's for sure, but it's great to my family.

The smell is descent and it's def. not oily, but I can't say I have found any benefit to using it over regular lotion. I'm willing to try out the Very Dry Skin version, however as others have pointed out- this lotion requires more effort than regular lotion. The amount of time you spend spreading this on and then rinsing it off leads to longer showers which defeats the purpose. I could just spend that time putting on regular lotion. It's definitely a niche product. Seems others like it a lot. Me, not so much.

column13: Used to yawn at a Braun...

First time out with this shaver today. Some slight irritation but went over my whole face several times. Used a pre-shave splash then shaved with this shaver. I started off today with a three day stubble after using my Gillette ($20.00 for four heads) by the way. This shaver does a superb job on the stubble (my beard grows very slow so it was more of a "shadow-stubble) and that's the trick. As soon as my beard was long enough to shave, I tackled it with my Braun. It very much exceeded my expectations!
However in my case the long whiskers of my mustache required the pop up trimmer to knock it down and the foils cleaned it up very nicely.
So in all, I definitely recommend this shaver highly and especially for younger men just beginning to develop a beard.
My best advice, as with other electrics I've used... Shave as often as you can. The shorter your beard the better the results.

column6: Tweezerman G.E.A.R. Ingrown Hair SplinterTweeze
column13: The best needle-tipped tweezers you'll ever find. Period. Buy them now.
column14:
You know when you have an ingrown hair, or a blackhead, or a splinter, or a speck of something somewhere it shouldn't be? And you know how conventional tweezers, with their lateral slanted edges, are still just too big to grab whatever that bothersome thing is?

Well, fear no more. The Tweezerman G.E.A.R. Ingrown Hair/Splinter Tweezer is here to save the day.

Yes, they're a bit expensive, and no, the needle tips aren't perfect for everything you would need tweezers for -- but they are so precise and work so well, they're worth the money. You have to be careful to keep the ends covered while not in use (it comes with a small silicone 'barrel cover') because they are, indeed, very sharp. Even so, the precision and high-tolerance manufacturing of the product make it truly quality.

Get these and a regular set of slant-edged tweezers, and you're set. Tweezerman even has a lifetime warranty, so you can send in dull Tweezers and have them sent back to you like new -- free of charge.

5/5, and if I ever lose these, you can be sure I'll be buying them again.

column6: Herbal Essences Hair Mousse 6.8 Oz, Pack of 3
column14: I decided to try this mousse because I've seen great reviews as far as using it on curly AND fine hair, which is my case. I've used it a few times now (my hair is just above the shoulders) and have some mixed feelings, though I am leaning towards using it going forward, especially during the summer months, when frizz is an issue. I will typically scrunch it into my wet hair, together with a leave-in conditioner (I've found that it doesn't provide enough volume on its own for me), air dry for some time and then blow-dry on hot/low with a diffuser, while scrunching & separating the curls. I then use a strong hair spray to help maintain the volume throughout the day (my hair is really fine).  The one big CON I have for this product is that it leaves my hair feeling REALLY dry to the touch (thus 4 stars vs. 5), which is a shame, because I've used products that make it feel really soft and I miss that effect. However.....it does get rid of frizz, adds shine to my hair, and, most importantly, maintains my style (volume & all) ALL DAY LONG! This is really incredible because, no matter which products I'd tried in the past (and there'd been lots!), my hair will become limp/flat by mid-afternoon and I'd have to use more hair spray to bring it back to life. However, with this mousse, my hair stays exactly the same until I go to bed at night, despite the heat & humidity, which is INCREDIBLE. I think that benefit alone is worth continuing to use this product. After all, everyone can see my hair, but far less people will be touching it. :) Overall, I recommend.

column6: Reusable Premium Cosmetic Makeup Sponge Egg Drop Applicator Smooth Puff Foundation Blender for Beauty by JGOB
column14: Decent dupe for authentic Beauty Blender and Real Techniques sponges. When moistened, JGOB (why this name?? sounds so weird) softens nicely--but it's almost too soft.  It doesn't have the nice supple 'bounce' that the Beauty Blender has when applying makeup; however, it does perform better than other no-name similar sponges. I've tried out cheaper variations of these types of makeup sponges from different companies and they are often too solid in texture (even after moistened) that they're very uncomfortable to use. The formulation of how these makeup sponges are made DOES make a difference in the finished effect of makeup application and use.  My first choice would be the authentic Beauty Blender if you can afford it, an excellent and very affordable 2nd choice would be the Real Techniques miracle complexion sponge, and a good 3rd option would be JGOB.

I don't find the 2 steps to be "too much" for my morning brushes. I actually like that it keeps me in check with spending a decent amount of time brushing my teeth! Step 1 is the cleanser and I feel a great clean when I use it. Step 2 is the whitening gel which I like to use and see my teeth look a little more sparkly after.

Results: After using for about a month I don't notice tremendous differences in the coloring of my teeth. They have gotten slightly whiter but have not progressed since then. I feel that this stuff is only good until a certain extent of whiteness. If you are looking for tremendous changes you won't find it here. If you are looking for a shade or 2 difference, then this stuff works. Once I got to my whiteness level, I've been able to maintain with the use of this product. My guess would be that this would be a really great after-care product if you had your teeth whitened professionally as it would probably maintain really well.

Sensitivity: While brushing, I notice certain spots in my mouth hurt a little. I think that means I have to go to the dentist honestly and have a cavity filled. Otherwise, I have not felt any sensitivity afterwards or throughout the day AT ALL. When I used the Crest White Strips I had serious sensitivity issues. Not with this stuff.

All in all, this product did its job and I am happy. If I could improve it, I would make the whitening results more intense, but for what it does it is great.

column14: Very disappointed in this sunblock. I have used many other Honest products and have liked them all, but this was a bust. They don't complain at all with other brands, but I thought if it worked well, they could deal with it, since it's better for them than other brands. There also for a very curved nailbed which I don't have so I can't get them to adhere thoroughly. They have been staying on, since I've tried to just  repair the split when  I don't have time to change them out.  The glue  that came with the multipack  dried out within a day or two after opening but I don't consider that to be a big deal, just an annoyance. (Random events can cause that in cyanoacrylate or almost any adhesive. It's stuns me when someone trashes an entire product  or product line  because the micro tube of glue has cured.  Glue costs $.98 or less.  Keep some on hand. It isn't difficult.) I'm pretty disappointed in these nails so I'll keep buying the Kiss products from my local grocery store.

column6: 100% Pure & Natural Herbs, Multi-Purpose Use, Food Spices, hair conditioning, herbal supplements & skin care
column14:
I've used blonde tint on my dark dishwater blonde hair all my life so that my long thick hair is medium to light blonde. I worry about irritation to my scalp and possible hair loss, so decided to try a henna product. I have white outgrowth (roots) on the top and crown of my head, and grayish brown roots in the back. I LOVE this product and use only this to touch up my roots on the top of my head. Mixed with only lemon juice to a thin yogurt consistency, leaving it on my roots for 2 hours, it completely changes my white roots to blonde...completely. The last hour I cover the rest of my hair (outer layer) with the cassia to enhance the color and condition my already blonde (from processing over the years )hair so it blends. HOWEVER, this product will not lighten or change the color of my gray/brown outgrowth; so I still have to use a regular blonde tint on the roots of the rest of my head. So, My hair project takes a few hours each month.

First, i make 1/4 inch parts all over the back and lower sides of my head (NOT where I have white outgrowth), then apply blonde tint to the outgrowth only, and leave it on 30 minutes or so according to directions. Then I wash and dry my hair. Next I mix the Cassie with lemon juice and let it sit about a half hour. Then I make narrow parts on the top of my head, then apply the cassia henna to the roots on top and crown of my head with a thin paint brush. Letting it sit for an hour, the mixture cools my scalp. After an hour passes, I paint the remaining henna over my entire outer layers of hair, roots to end, let it sit for another hour, and wash completely. It's time consuming but perfect for me.

column6: Jurlique Herbal Recovery Advanced Serum
column13: lovely scent, non-irritating, but I can't really tell that it's doing anything
column14:
This is gentle on my skin and has not caused any irritation, despite the strong fragrance (rose). I think it's moisturizing, which is great. I've been using it for a few weeks, though, and I'm not sure what effects I'm supposed to be seeing. "Herbal recovery" is kind of vague and generic as a term.

You can see the full ingredients list if you scroll down the product page (this matches the official list). This contains niacinamide, which is in a lot of brightening skin preparations. And I have had reduced redness lately, so this may be contributing (although it is not the only brightening product I have used lately, so I can't attribute the change solely to this product, I can only say that niacinamide has definitely worked for me in the past).

I like all the plant extracts and think they might be useful during the summer after sun exposure (rose fruit, for example, is high in vitamin C, an antioxidant). Despite the different elements in this product, it has a smooth formula that stays well blended and uniform in consistency. It dries quickly and the scent fades fairly quickly as well. Some of the plant extracts may have slight antibacterial effects, as well (rosemary, lavender). I wouldn't rely on them exclusively to prevent skin infections, but they will probably help a little bit.

I think the product description section is incorrect, though. This does not contain Persian silk extract (verified by looking at the ingredients list here as well as the one at Jurlique's site) nor does it contain wu zhu yu (evodia) extract.

In the end, although I can see how many of the ingredients listed should lead to positive effects, I just can't say with certainty that any of them are actually causing a significant change in the appearance of my skin.

column13: A well-designed shaver for all-around use
column14: For my personal shaving needs, I tend to prefer a trimmer rather than a rotary blade (or whatever the terminology is for this). But the last trimmer I owned--a Wahl model--lasted less than a year. The rechargeable battery gave out, so that it would run only about 15 seconds, and plugging it in won't bypass the battery so it's not usable, and to replace the battery I'd have to mail it in and pay more than I spent on the shaver initially. This shaver was, for me, a slight compromise, because it has only a small trimmer blade and mainly serves as the close shaver with the rotary blade. That said, the battery stays charged so long that I rarely need to plug it in, and if the battery did wear out, I'll still be able to use it by plugging it in. The little trimmer blade works okay. The head and blades are amazingly easy to keep clean by rinsing. And, indeed, the rotary blades give a closer shave, handy on the rare occasions where a perfect shave is necessary to go with a rented tuxedo.

column6: CeraVe Facial Moisturizing Lotion PM 3 oz, Face Moisturizer for Nighttime Use
column14:
I'm in my late thirties, so I've started a full-time battle against wrinkles.

I go to an amazing dermatologist who recommended CeraVe PM. She raved about its price as her office sold a nearly identical product for $150 per 2 fluid ounces. She uses it daily which says a lot considering all of the product samples and freebies she has at her disposal. She assigned the following as my nightly anti-wrinkle protocal: 1. wash face with Clarisonic using Cetaphil, 2. apply Atralin (wait at least twenty minutes before step 3), 3. apply CeraVe P.M.

Use it every night for at least a month and you will be hooked.

column6: Shea Butter
column13: This Better Shea Butter is INCREDIBLE
column14:
I am a believer in Unrefined Ivory Shea Butter by Better Shea Butter from Better Shea Butter. I have worked in construction for thirty years and my skin has taken a beating from dust, dirt, wind, severe cold and extreme heat. Of course I didn't take good care of my skin except the once in a while squirt of brand name lotions filled with ingredients that sound like they were imported from some intergalactic trade agreement we have with the planet Uranus.
Well I have developed super dry cracking skin on my hands and spots on my legs and arms. After months of regularly applying the lotions mentioned above I had no improvement in my skin (I had to get serious now right?). Of course an immediate relief was obtained when the chemical laced lotions were applied but it lasted a matter of thirty to sixty minutes then it was back to scratching, rubbing and constant discomfort. No over the counter OR prescription (more ingredients from Uranus) lotions or creams helped in the long haul nor did they start to HEAL my skin (I was hideous).
I had to get really serious now. I did research and found great articles and reviews about Shea Butter and home made lotions that contained Shea Butter.
KEEP READING... I KNOW THIS IS LONG BUT I HAD THIS CONDITION FOR A LONG MISERABLE TIME.
I purchased this Shea Butter I received it on Friday. I applied it to the problem areas twice a day for two days and I can see AND feel my skin healing. My left hand by the fatty part by the thumb was cracked, red like a tomato and oozing nastiness. I applied the Shea Butter extra heavy in that area and I am writing this Sunday morning and that area's color is almost normal and the deep painful cracks are well on their way of being closed and healed. I am a true believer in two days that I purchased everything Better Shea Butter has on their website.
Try this product IT WORKS!!!! incredible

I have a bottle of rose absolute, which is what I usually purchase; however, I was looking for something portable and with a roller-ball applicator. After reading the reviews for this product, I thought that I had found what I needed.

However, this scent does not compare to my rose absolute, and it makes me sneeze.

I did have a great deal more luck with Kuumba's Tea Rose, which is barely discriminable from rose absolute, does not "mutate", does not seem to upset my allergies, nor make me feel as if I should pay a visit to the mausoleum.

column6: Physicians Formula Mineral Wear Face Powder Compact .3 oz (9 g)
column13: Great for summer!  And use the brush to clean your computer keyboard!
column14: One of my favorite powder foundations.  I use this primarily in the summer because it doesn't "melt" off of my face in the dry summer heat of Colorado.  It is a little messier than a talc-based powder (which I actually have nothing against), but MUCH less messy than a loose mineral powder.  I apply lightly, over moisturizer and primer, with a Ecotools retractable kabuki brush--works great!  I set it with ELF setting spray, and it does not budge, or change color, all day.  I like the SPF, too.  It's very affordable for a mineral foundation.  I also like that it is one of the few mineral powders that does NOT contain bismuth oxychloride, which I have a terrible reaction to.  I find the product to be slightly drying, but since I use moisturizer on the dry areas first, this is not a problem.  Would love a better color selection.  TIP:  the brush is the best computer keyboard cleaner EVER!

column13: Excellent for kids.  Not totally intuitive..and app is only for ios, not android.  Like the feature for toothpaste application
column14:
The Sonicare Kids toothbrush is a great electric toothbrush in and of itself for kids. The grip is well designed for easy handling and easy cleaning. It also has a nice feature on the handle that allows the toothbrush to rest on the counter (bristle side up) for a neat toothpaste application. The bristle head is substantial for all-over cleaning.

The gradually increasing timer system is not intuitive and requires a quick read of the instructions to get the maximum out of this teaching tool. Without reading it first, it is hard to know the difference between beeps .

Instructions say there is an Android app available but there isn't at this time.... wasn't too happy I wasted time looking.

column6: Bed Head Curling/styling Iron, Purple, BH327
column14: Best curling iron I have ever used. I usually straighten my hair, so I'm more accustom to using a straightening iron. I have always had trouble figuring out how to get my hair to have beachy waves with a curling iron, so I basically stopped trying. When I saw this iron, and viewed a video on youtube on how to use it, I decided to give it a try (especially since it's so cheap!). I am so glad I tried it. I have wavy/curly hair naturally, but my waves/curls are all over the place and uneven. I usually let my hair air dry 80% then blow dry it the rest of the way. This gives me a straightish look, with some waves. After it's dry, it takes me maybe 5 minutes to put in perfectly even waves. I love how easily my hair falls between the bumps with no effort. I only hold it in place for about 3-4 seconds and my waves come out perfectly every time!

column6: Double Edge Safety Razor
column14:
Bought this as a travel razor, but it's contending for daily use. I was surprised how well this shaved.

My current daily razor is a Merkur 43C which I love, but as a two piece I didn't want to risk damage to the long screw by packing it. So I opted for the three-piece Kelvin at roughly half the price for its flatter packing profile.

From a shaving perspective it is first rate as the shave it provides is of high quality. I was able to do a three-pass without irritation. Having large hands, I held the handle with three fingers like a chop stick or pen. Using this approach allowed for a functional and reasonably pleasant shave. However, I removed a star because I find the handle to be the weak link in the design. It is shorter, lighter, and the knurling provides less grip than I had hoped. This traits would push it out of day to day use for me.

Note: Be sure to assemble it correctly. My first use had the middle piece inverted. There was zero blade gap and therefore zero shaving. I was ready to return it, finding it useless. Once I realized my error (bottom plate has an indentation for the handle) and assembled it correctly, I was able to get one of the best shaves I ever had. I think one of the earlier reviewers may have made this error, because they complained the razor's mildness was off the charts.

I'm now on the hunt or a stainless steel handle that addresses the Kelvin's weight, length and grip limitations, once that is in hand I foresee a frankenrazor that will be seeing daily duty and not occasional travel use. Great tool with a minor mod.

Update... I ended up paired a 4" heavy steel handle from a Mac razor and could not be happier. While I still prefer the Merkur's shave the Kelvin will see occasional daily duty going forward.

column13: Bargain razor gets the job done.
column14: This shaver gives me a reasonable shave, although when I was younger and had a heavier beard, I might have needed a 5 o'clock touchup. The shave is consistent with other foil shavers I've had in the past.  This one runs slower than previous models, but I'm not convinced that's a bad thing.  It's less noisy than the previous model, but still cuts well.  I don't experience any razor burn or pulling.  I think that only happens when you press too hard.  Stretching the skin is helpful.  The razor doesn't do particularly well with the longer, softer hair on the neck.  I use the slide-out trimmer to take a first pass in that case, followed by using the foil cutters.  No electric shaver I've ever had matches a blade razor and this one is no exception.  But I knew that going in.  The low cost of this razor makes it a bargain purchase.

column6: Hair Therapy Wrap - Coco - Cordless Thermal Turban Heat Wrap
column13: Works great at deep conditioning my hair with the added heat
column14:
This review is for the Hair Therapy Wrap - Coco - Cordless Thermal Turban Heat Wrap.

This is an interesting and very functional hair wrap. The wrap comes to you flat without any of the heating packs inside. I didn‚Äôt realize this to begin with, but that is actually very smart. I can remove the packs and wash the turban anytime I want! So I actually prefer the way they put it together.

The turban comes with 1 long heating pack that threads in through the front of the hat and into the back cover to get all of your hair if it is long. Then there are two side heating packs. The packs secure into the compartments with Velcro. It is easy to assemble and very secure once you get the packs in place.

The material is sort of a towel material. It is very soft and comfortable. I secured my packs into my turban and heated the whole thing in the microwave. It was ready to go in seconds, and went on easy and tied well with the flaps. I had coconut oil on my hair and was conditioning it all night. It was comfortable and nice to have the warm turban wrapped on my head.

The extra heat on my hair while conditioning really made a difference. I found the coconut oil penetrated deeper into my hair shafts and scalp‚Ä¶. My hair was ultra soft the next few days from my treatment and I think it was due to the fact I had this wonderful heating cap.

5/5 stars for functionality, materials and design.

If you have any questions please post below and I would be happy to answer! I received a discounted promotional sample of this item for my honest and unbiased review.

column6: Cute Floral Makeup Bag for Travel and Home Perfect For Your Makeup and Cosmetics
column13: Gotta Have More Bella and Bear!!!
column14:
I love Bella and Bear products! I was first introduced to this company last week and honestly I can't get enough!!! Bella and Bear have a long line of makeup and beauty accessories to keep you styling all day long. There is a classic beautiful floral print that I love, that is on all of their products. I love that Bella and Bear really took the time to pay attention to details big and small, from the heart shaped zipper pulls on the makeup bag to the beautifully decorated box the makeup bag was stored in.

I decided to read up on my new found obsession by visiting the Bella and Bear website. www.bellaandbearblog.com I love the back story just as much as I love the products. Bella and Bear are the kitties that stole their heart. As a owner of two kitties myself I can totally understand. Maybe I should start a company and name it after my kitties. How does Muffin and Moonshine sound? Nah...I'll leave this up to the professionals, Bella and Bear. Unfortunately Bear took a journey to the rainbow bridge and it left a void in everyone's heart that only Bear II could fill. Now everyone is happy again but Bear is certainly not forgotten and the spirit of the love of all three animals can be felt through their products.

This makeup bag is amazing. I just happened to be spending the night at my boyfriend's house last night so I decided to use this bag so I can review it at the same time. This is a good size bag with a washable fabric for a quick and easy clean-up. There are two handles for easy carrying and my favorite part of the bag are the two heart shaped zipper pulls.

Now, you could fill this bag with makeup until your heart's content but I used it for a little bit of everything (toiletries and makeup) for an overnight stay to see my bae. When you pull on those awesome heart shaped zipper pulls to get to the amazing inside of the bag you will notice that the compartments are clear! No more fumbling through pockets to just find that mascara you were looking for. Now you can do what I call the \\\see and grab\\\\\". It's very easy to do, first you locate the item you are looking for (see) and then you unzip the compartment and grab it. Voila! Easy Peasy.

On the inside of the bag there are four zippered compartments, two large and two small. There is also a very cool and convenient hook so once you unzip your bag you can hang it for easy access to all of your precious products. I was more excited to pack up this bag with overnight necessities than I was to actually spend time with my boyfriend. Shhhh....don't tell him I said that. I took lots of pictures to share in this review.

Here is how I packed up my bag.

Large Compartment #1
*Facial Cleaner
*Bar of Soap
*Deodorant
*Body Moisturizer (it's hiding under the zipper down the middle)

Large Compartment #2
*Mouthwash
*Toothbrush
*Toothpaste

Small Compartment #1
*Several Makeup Brushes

Small Compartment #2
*Mascara
*2 Eyeshadow Pots
*Lippie

As you can tell I was able to stuff a lot of goodies into this bag. There was definitely room for more but that's all I needed. It zipped up fine and fit perfectly in my overnight bag. To sum it up, I can't say enough great things about this bag, it's so awesome, and the brand is super cute with a sweet backstory. You can tell the quality and love put into these products and I wont stop buying them until I have them all.

column6: Silk18 Natural Hair Conditioner Argan Oil Sulfate Free Treatment for Dry and Damaged Hair Silk Amino Acids Jojoba & Keratin All Hair Types Women & Men & Teens Safe for Color Treated Hair
column14: I've been doing no-poo for over two months and needed something to help my hair from breaking at the ends. Just the slightest pull and my hair would snap, there was no elasticity despite trying coconut oil masks or egg/avocado masks on an almost daily basis. My poor hair has had to deal with hard water in the past and just hasn't ever been strong since. I did some research and found that when people have low elasticity in their hair they either do better with a natural oil like coconut oil or with protein. I decided to try and look for a protein based conditioner that was natural so that it wouldn't weigh down my hair with nasty chemicals. I have shoulder length hair that I wash with sifted rye flour (best no-poo shampoo I've tried) or occasionally a whole egg. This silk conditioner works wonderfully as is or as a leave in treatment. My hair is so noticeably soft and not heavy or greasy. I totally LOVE the scent and I think my family prefers it far more than the apple cider vinegar rinses I've used in the past. I love how natural the ingredients are and how strong and healthy my hair feels now. I have tried a few other products including: Hydrating Argan Oil Hair Mask and Deep Conditioner By Arvazallia, It's a 10 Miracle Leave-in Product and DermOrganic Leave-In Treatment, and none of these items helped but I think it has to do with the fact that my hair does not want oil per say but a protein instead.

column13: Your skin will thank you! Great Exfoliant!
column14: This product is an amazing exfoliant! It has helped improve the appearance of my skin by minimizing the appearance of scars on my chin, and evening out my skin tone. I use this product only once a week, and one tube lasts several months for me. I have used other exfoliants in the past including St. Ives Apricot scrub, Olay Fresh Effects, Neutrogena Deep Clean, L'Oreal Go 360 Deep Clean, and Suki Exfoliate Foaming Cleanser (which is a close second), but this is my favorite. It has a thick, concentrated consistency which makes it easy to use. I have found that some exfoliants contain too creamy of a base so that you can't feel the exfoliant really working on your skin. I recommend applying using small circular motions and focusing on your problem areas. I clean my forehead, nose, and chin well and then gently exfoliate the rest of my face. I wouldn't recommend this product for everyday use if you have normal skin because it will probably be too much. I use a foaming cleaner between uses. This is my favorite exfoliating product and I recommend it to all my friends and family. I think it is well worth the price.

column6: Advanced Anti Aging Cream With Matrixyl, Hyaluronic Acid, Shea Butter And  Green Tea Extract,  Natural Wrinkle Reducing Formula,  Normal, Oily, And Dry Skin, For Men And Women
column13: Great for Oily and Sensitive Skin
column14:
Today I am going to be looking at Peels & Petals Anti-Aging Moisturizer with Matrixyl for all skin types.
I have tried the moisturizer for almost a month now, so I feel as if I can give a comprehensive and detailed review of its results and how I turned out using it.

First let me give you a rundown of the product, what it promises and its cost and then we will go into how I used it and what results I had.

Product Info: Peels & Petals Anti-Aging Moisturizer
This product boasts age erasing power thanks to the combination of Matrixyl, Green Tea, and Hyaluronic Acid. The makers also state that this product will contribute to evening the skin tone, leaving the skin well hydrated, and improving skin elasticity.

The moisturizer is paraben and sulfate free, which makes it gentle and easy to use for all skin types according to the makers and contains a variety of more natural ingredients like witch hazel and shea butter.

My Personal Results

I have two problems with my skin that makes it quite difficult to find a sufficient and well performing moisturizer. First, I have very oily skin and this can cause a huge problem with overly oily moisturizers that leave my skin feeling oily and more prone to breakouts. Second, my skin is ultra sensitive, and at times, is so sensitive that I have to use special soaps just to wash or it will be painful and break-out. With this in mind I always try moisturizers that boast an ease of use for sensitive skin or all skin types so when I read this, I was hopeful, but not expectant...because I am often let down.

1. My oily skin was not a problem with the Peels & Petals moisturizer, it actually worked great and did not leave my skin feeling oily at all. The moisturizer is thicker and absorbs quickly, leaving little to no residue. This means that it does not clog or add to any sort of oil on my face. I found that VERY impressive....I also liked the fresh/clean fragrance.

2. As for my sensitive skin...for the most part, it did not agitate my skin very much or at all. My skin can be more sensitive on some days than others, and there were a few times when I felt a slight bit of agitation from the product after application, but that was not every day and it was not enough to where I felt like I needed to discontinue my usage or that it was the moisturizer itself causing the agitation. Overall, I thought that Peels & Petals stayed true to its promise.

3. My skin felt hydrated and tighter after a few weeks of usage. I will admit I am most impressed with the lack of residue or oily feeling after application with the result of a hydrated face that is not sticky or shiny. I have no skin tone issues, so I cannot speak to dark spot removal or management...but overall I felt this moisturizer did the job and worked rather well.

Peels & Petals is a great product and worth the money....if you are looking for a hydrating and anti-aging cream that does not leave your face oily...this is the one for you.

This was a product test where the maker provided the product to me at no cost in exchange for my honest and unbiased review, I was not paid for this test.r />
