column6: Natural Aqua Gel Cure 250ml
column14:
I have to say how surprised I am to read that there is anyone out there who isn't completely in love with this product! Using this 2-3 times a week helps to keep my skin looking much more smooth, soft, and radiant than ever before. The thorough exfoliation helps to keep breakouts to a minimal and helps heal acne marks more quickly.
I have read that a lot of skeptics say the product is just balling up and it's not actually removing dead skin at all. Well then how else does it remove less skin if I repeat the process 2-3 times in a row and begin to reveal more shiny, new skin with a slight tingling sensation?! Also, I used this several days in a row on my forehead after getting a sunburn that left me peeling horribly bad on vacation. It kept my peeling down to a minimum while I was out and about and removed SO much skin before I applied my makeup.
Maybe it is possible that the product does somewhat ball up as it removes dead skin. I don't really know. Either way, I know that this product does work and it will improve the appearance of your skin!

column13: Spend a bit more and get Conair's 1875W Tourmaline hair drier.
column14: I had this hair dryer for a few years but it recently just died when I dropped it on my bathroom floor. The hair dryer functioned OK and you'll notice noticeably less hair static and frizz compared to non-ionic driers. However, I suggest that you consider paying a little more for a better Conair's 225NP 1875 watt Tourmaline Ceramic hair dryer. I always found Revlon's rear vent frustratingly difficult to clean, and I actually had to use vacuum attachments to clean out the accumulated lints and fuzz on the grill. Conair's is a simple flip out grill with a smooth filter that I can simply wipe off easy. The Revlon dryer frequently sparked internally while in use for no apparent reason, and it was much louder and blowed noticeably weaker than Conair's that I recently got as a replacement. Do yourself a favor and spend a bit extra for an appliance you'll use daily for next several years.

column6: Majestic Pure Grade A Unrefined Organic Shea Butter, 12 oz
column13: Can't wait to make my own beauty bars!
column14:
I have used many products with shea butter in them and they are always so nourishing to my skin. I suffer from ichythosis vulgaris, so my skin is often flaky and scaly. Since I was tired of paying high prices for various lotions, I decided to try making my own. To that end, I bought this unrefined organic shea butter in order to get the highest quality I could.

When I received it, I was surprised that it hadn't melted, as it was sitting out in 100 degree heat for a few days while we were on a family getaway. But it was packaged nicely, with wax paper inside of a cardboard box. It smelled quite nice when I opened it. I immediately ran my fingers over it a few times, and it melted enough to leave a small film over my finger. I used this on one arm and then left it for 24 hours just to see if I could tell a difference. The arm I put the shea butter on was quite soft after a full day, while my other arm had already started to dry out. This alone filled me with confidence!

I have been collecting many recipes to make my own beauty bars, and I can't wait to try them all. I think having this will make all the difference in quality, AND I'll have saved money!!

I received a discount on this item in order to review, but all opinions are honest and my own.

column6: Antifungal Soap with Tea Tree Oil, Helps Treat & Wash Away Athletes Foot, Ringworm, Nail Fungus, Jock Itch, Body Odor & Acne. Antibacterial Defense Against Bacteria Related Skin Irritations 9oz.
column13: I am so far very pleased with the product
column14: I am so far very pleased with the product. I chose to dilute it with pure filtered water and put it in a spray bottle. This was easier for me to handle and use in the shower for my particular condition.  I am recovering from a crazy case of cellulitis, and am unsure what might have started it--fungus is suspect but because there is no obvious wound or obvious fungal issue is also unconfirmed--have been on crazy antibiotics for over a month which create their own issues especially in warm creases when you are asked to always sit with your leg elevated and need to be careful with compromised skin. Antibiotics alone didn't do it for me. 4 ER visits and three hospital admissions later I decided to inform my doctor exactly what I would be doing at home. Gave them a chance to observe me with these treatments in the hospital, and advocated for what I know about my own body.  I read reviews on many products and also checked ingredient lists.  I chose this product for natural ingredients and reviews that addressed actual fungal issues that were helped, rather than the smell or how good skin feels.  I like natural, organic ingredients as I am allergic to many things artificial and pharmaceutical- which was part of my problem with even the most gentle standard hospital treatments.  Some of the most noticeable improvement for me has been on the back of one very expensive bio-available drug, lots of lyposomal vitamin C, probiotics, digestive enzymes, diluted apple cider vinegar rinses, showers with this product, and tea tree oil/vitamin E carefully applied directly to dry skin. Then large ace bandage wraps for swelling and to protect the compromised skin. Just my experience, and although I was firm, my doctor was informed and included and listened to. I have some wonderful nurse friends and work with a medical assistant/ massage therapy department at work. Best of both worlds for this nasty stubborn infection.  Respect your medical professionals, but if it isn't working, it isn't working.  Customer service is prompt and superb too.

With the growing market for beard washes it can be hard to tell which is worth your hard earned money. While this is a very small bottle of wash (almost travel size like) a little bit goes a long way. Percy Nobleman beard wash doesn't lather very heavy and the scent isn't anything to brag about, but it does deliver a well moisturized beard that is soft to the touch and very manageable afterwards. Even after a light blow drying and brushing my beard wasn't overly dried. All in all the beard wash seems to be made of great ingredients as I've found most of the french hygiene products are. The bottle that I received had a best if used by date of 1/10/16

The price is a bit high for the amount of wash you get but if you're looking for great results and more beard management I'd recommend giving this a try!

column14:
Effective lip stain didn't dry, crack or peel off as other lip stain brands have, after 3+ hrs of wear which included 2 cocktails, 3 glasses of water, a few appetizer bites and lots of laughs. The consistency is a bit watery, not as thick as other brands, which surprised me‚Äîindeed, quite lightweight, as advertised.
1 coat delivers fuschia, 2 coats gave me the elusive, perfect, overripe raspberry color seen [and coveted!] in lipstick commercials, especially after dabbing a bit of clear lip gloss on. Once both layers were dry, I did a kiss test on my hand with great results: zero lip marks! After 4 hrs, feathering was minimal (concealer and light powder on lip line may have helped). Product page in website advertises 4 hrs of wear‚Äîit certainly delivered what it promised. Great product for the price!

The **only** drawback may be that it can be a bit difficult to remove: I scrubbed lips with make-up remover-soaked tissue and hardly got any off. Whoa‚Äîthis IS a lip stain! I had to brush lips along with mouth at bedtime to effectively take it off. It may be a plus for some, negative for those who want a blank canvas for a totally different lipstick color. I myself don't mind.

column6: Professional Eyelash Curler - Never Needs Refill Pads! - Doesn't Pinch Or Pull! - Best Curl For Fuller Eyelashes With Cute Pink Packaging
column13: Not the right shape - pinched my eyelids
column14:
This curler did not work for me at all. The promise of no pinching was simply not met.

First, I'll explain why I was looking for a new curler. I've had the same Revlon curler for probably 20 years and have loved it. Only recently, I ran out of the old refill pads for it and can only find the new silicone ones. They just weren't staying in place and popped out at the ends.

The idea of not needing refill pads is what brought me to this curler. I almost didn't buy it because it looked like most reviews were written in exchange for a free curler. I thought this might be giving it a distorted and not accurate high rating. Giving the company the benefit of the doubt, I tried it anyway. Needless to say, my review is true and honest and not driven by receiving the product for free.

When it arrived and I tried it, I was unable to use it without pinching my eyelids. The problem is the curve on this curler is VERY shallow. I attached pictures of it next to my old Revlon curler to illustrate the difference. I suppose this product could work for people with shallow set eyes, but with average depth in my eyes I just couldn't grab the lashes. What happened is, I could grasp a few lashes in the center and then the ends of the curler would grab my lids instead as it didn't curve down/ in far enough to reach the rest of the lashes. It was awkward, painful, and completely not functional. Because it didn't meet the "no pinching" promise, I returned it.

To be fair, the company refunded my money and was all around pleasant in my experience with them. For that reason, I might have given this 2 stars. I opted for 1 star instead because I do think the seeded reviews are giving people a misleading average rating.

In the end I went back to my old Revlon curler and bent the metal a little bit with some needle nose pliers to hold the silicone refill in place. It worked like a charm. :)

column14:

the color of label is NOT light blue, the word "cool" is not on the label and the gel is not "cool" or mentholated.

After placing a complaint, the rescinded the demand for the restocking fee

Buyer beware...what u see on the ad is NOT what will arrive if u order this

Having said all this, Nivea Sensitive Gel is a great product

BUT CAN ANYONE RECOMMEND A GOOD MENTHOLATED SHAVING GEL. Edge, many years ago, made one, but stopped

column6: Murray & Lanman Orange Blossom Cologne 4 Fl Oz
column13: Excellent for Bringing Back Memories~Awful if You Want A Real Orange Blossom Perfume
column14:
This is exactly what I thought it would be.

I grew up in a small citrus town in south Florida. Every year, we'd make the trek up to Webb's Citrus Candy Factory and buy candy and orange blossom perfume (we would save our allowance because it cost a whole seventy-five cents!)

I bought this for sentimental reasons and got exactly what I thought I would.

If you're looking for a great orange blossom perfume, this is definitely not it. If you were raised in a small citrus town and thought this was a very big deal (buying our own perfume!), then it'll bring back wonderful memories and your husband will ask you why you're wearing it.

column6: Best Anti Aging Moisturizer Face Cream, Shea Butter, Jojoba & Macadamia Seed Oil, and Patented L22 Complex From YEOUTH, Hydrates, Firms, Erases Wrinkles and Evens Skin Tone - Day and Night Cream
column13: Not a \fountain of Yeouth\" but a nice moisturizer"
column14:
I've used a lot of anti-aging moisturizers, but I've never had the opportunity to try Yeouth until recently. Nothing will completely stop aging, but a great moisturizer is a critical part of slowing down the process. Here are my takeaways from Yeouth:

Pros
*Nice and thick but not greasy or heavy when applied
*Convenient, functional pump to measure the amount needed (face and neck, roughly a dollop the size of a pea needed)
*Skin looks and feels smooth, soft, and beautiful
*Several natural ingredients good for the skin such as aloe and grapeseed oil
*Formulation is good for all skin types provided the specific individual has no allergies to any of the ingredients. Always check your labels.
*Small vial but will last awhile due to the small amount needed to moisturize the skin

Cons

*Contains polysorbate 60 where studies from the 1950's showed potential for cancer but only in high dosages. Highly outdated research but more needed.
*Contains tocopherol which isn't noted skin irritant but is an eye irritant. Use caution around the eye area.

Overall, it's a nice moisturizer to use but to see anti-aging benefits, long-term use is needed. Although I received this product at a discount for an honest review, I never guarantee a positive rating.

column6: Philips Norelco Rq12+ Replacement Head For Series 8000 (Sensotouch 3D) And Arcitec
column13: UPDATE- December 2015- I was shopping for a new shaver, as the original head was no longer giving satisfactory shaves.
column14:
When I first put it on the razor I noticed it did not shave as well as the "worn" head I was replacing. After a few months of trying to learn to like it, I put the old head back on (RQ12, NOT +). I found the old head still shaved better than the new one and I will use that until it no longer shaves me satisfactorily. Then I guess I will have to switch to another shaver as this replacement head is not acceptable. Poor shave, not close and it pulls hairs. I spoke to tech support at Phillips and they seemed to be aware of the issue but said that corporate has not announced any plan to fix the issue. One post said the newer cutters from the current razor will fit the RQ12+, but the tech guy tried it while he had me on the line and said they do not fit. So for now the razor is useless once the original cutters wear out.
UPDATE: Dec 2015- As mentioned above I put the original head back on, planning to replace the shaver once that head was no longer working. On checking the reviews for various shavers I noticed the Norelco reviews, especially for the RQ-12+ changed after about Dec. 2014 and were more mixed. The more recent purchasers seemed more positive by a margin that made me believe a redesign must have taken place. I decided to give it one more try before chucking the shaver and ordered another replacement head. Both the new RQ 12+ and the old one look the same to my eye, but the shave is night and day different. On first use my impression was "I got my favorite shaver back!" as it shaves like it did when I first bought it. Not sure what they changed, but after two weeks with the new head I am convinced either they improved the design of the RQ12+ or my previous one was defective. Either way I am pleased with the head now and have upped my rating- it would be higher, but I want to see how long this head lasts. If it makes it a year I will be most pleased.

column6: Professional Eyelash Curler - Never Needs Refill Pads! - Doesn't Pinch Or Pull! - Best Curl For Fuller Eyelashes With Cute Pink Packaging
column14:
This professional eyelash curler by liveWIRE is a decent eyelash curler. The grips have a bit of a "rubber" smell to them, though not overly strong. At first I wasn't sure if they helped or hindered, but after a few uses, I think that they help, making it easier to keep a steadier grip. They curl my lashes well, though after multiple tries and positions, I still can't get the longest straighter lashes on the outer section of my eyelashes to curl. I have yet to find an eyelash curler that will curl those up and they are the ones I want some curl in the most. I am also dubious about the no pinching, as I think that is largely due to user error, not an eyelash curler itself, and I almost always pinch myself occasionally with any curler.

I am not sure how I feel about the silicone strip never needing replacing. There were no instructions, but I'm assuming that means that it can be washed and it will retain its original shape rather than eventually get flattened down like regular ones do, but I'm still uncertain how cleanly that would be after a few years or if it will truly retain its shape for years. Only time can tell. Obviously, that would save money over the long run, so I am assuming that's why the higher price point than most other eyelash curls that are closer to half the price and work pretty much just as well. This one did seem to grip my eyelashes a bit better than my current one and that may be the silicone (or it could be mine needs a new pad).

column14:
Due to recently having cataract surgery, I have not been able to PROPERLY test the Fast Lash Growth Serum by iLuminate from Elite Beauty Cosmetics but I can honestly tell you following. I have used it on the eye that did not have the surgery. Perhaps that is going to be the best test of all in the long run because I'll be able to see how well it works. I received it late in the day 4 days ago and have been using it every day for 3 days.

It is super easy to apply. When opening the cap, it opens smoothly and the thin liner brush comes out with just the right amount to apply the clear liquid to the base of the upper eyelashes. I then dip it again and it comes out with just enough for the lower eyelashes. I apply it above the eyelashes on the top eyelashes and below the lashes on the bottom eyelashes. That way, I won't get any of it in my eyes. However, a couple of times my hand has slipped and I have gotten some in my eye. When that happened, I had NO adverse reaction.

I have also been applying it to my eyebrows. I am a natural blonde and my eyelashes and eyebrows have always been very light and sparse. Without makeup, I am pretty much without eyes so I'm hoping that my eyebrows will get darker and thicker over time just like I hope my eyelashes will.

My skin is very sensitive and very prone to being allergic to products I use on it. I have had NO allergic reaction to this product. The Fast Lash Growth Serum by iLuminate feels light on my skin, my eye has NOT watered excessively and I have felt NO irritation. I am happy with the product and can't wait until I am able to apply this to both eyes.

I was fortunate to receive this product at a discount in exchange for my HONEST & UNBIASED opinion. I ALWAYS pretest every product prior to writing a review. I am free to write whatever I believe to be true, whether positive or negative. This is my true story and my honest opinion.

column6: Mango Butter (16 Ounce) - Pure, Natural, Perfect For DIY Skin/Hair Care, Unscented
column14:
This was my first time to try Mango Butter and I'm impressed. This has virtually no fragrance and it melted cleanly when I made lotion today. I used a very simple recipe of 1/2 cup mango butter and 1 Tbsp each of Avocado oil and Apricot oil. Melted them together in a double boiler (a stainless steel mixing bowl over a pot of boiling water) then cooled the mixture in the refrigerator until it set and turned translucent. I then added 7 drops (I don't like much fragrance) of tea tree essential oil and blended it with a hand mixer for about 4 minutes until it turned creamy. Pour it in to a jar and it will set up to a firmer consistency. However, it melts back to an easily spreadable lotion when warmed in the hands in just seconds. Great stuff!! I'm delighted with how moisturizing it feels.

I'm allergic to shea butter and this will be my new go to butter!

column6: For Pro Ultrasonic Diffuser, Namaste
column14:
The only other experience I have had with a diffuser was the SAVASANA ULTRASONIC AROMA DIFFUSER from this same manufacturer. The NAMASTE ULTRASONIC AROMA DIFFUSER is plastic, but it has a nice imitation wood grain look on the bottom that sets it apart. To use you just remove the cover, add water, add a few drops of your desired oil, and then turn the diffuser on.

I was a little disappointed in the size of the water basin on this device. The Savasana held a whole pint of oil. The NAMASTE ULTRASONIC AROMA DIFFUSER only holds about half a cup. Therefore, it only works for about an hour.

There are three different mist modes. You can choose high, medium, or low. You get a good amount of mist on the highest setting, but instead of an hour, the water will be used up in about 50 minutes.

You can select and lock in a specific color for the light to remain. The colors are light blue, dark blue, green, dark green, purple, and red/pink. You can also choose to have the light loop through all the colors or turn them completely off.

The device uses no heat so is safe at the office or at home.

Overall, the NAMASTE ULTRASONIC AROMA DIFFUSER is a decent diffuser. I definitely enjoyed the SAVASANA ULTRASONIC AROMA DIFFUSER, however, because of the larger water reservoir. However, there are those who won't want a diffuser to be on for more than an hour and who prefer bigger lights. If that's the case then the Namaste might be for you.

I was provided a sample of this item from the manufacturer for examination and possible review.

column13: great set of tools with lots of variety
column14:
What an amazing kit. There are 5 tools in the kit along with a nice sturdy case. There are 3 double ended loop extractors and 2spoon extractors. Unfortunately, there are no instructions/guide as to what each tool and the tip does and what to use it on. Yes, i know its for blackheads but there are all different shapes and sizes.

I've been experimenting with them to see which ones did the best job. I found that the loop style ones were real easy and all you needed to do was basically swipe or comp the areas and it got a bunch of gunk. I found the loops to also leave the least amount of redness and irritation when done better than the spoon styles where it leaves circle red marks from the pressure.

There are plenty of videos online to see how to use the tools.

I really like them and also they are easy to clean using hot water and a little soap.

column6: Shea Moisture African Black Soap Deep Cleansing Shampoo - 13 oz.
column14: Keep in mind this product line is made for Black people, particularly those with natural hair. With that in mind this shampoo is NOT a regular shampoo. Most Black people, especially those who are natural hair, DONT shampoo their hair often and some not at all. Also, naturals tend to use a lot of products on their hair, which can cause product build up. This is a CLARIFYING shampoo, so it's meant to strip the hair and scalp of everything. Yes, it leaves some moisture, but only as much as a clarifying shampoo can. So, if you are of another race using this shampoo DO NOT think it is like a regular shampoo, because it's not. I don't recommend using this more than once a week, because it is geared towards a race who's hair and hair care needs aren't the same as yours. That's not to say you can't use this line, but to better assist anyone with using this.

column13: An excellent purchase, two years later...
column14: EDIT:  It's been two years since I originally posted this review. I update it now to say that the wash cloths have held up very well to normal daily use and washings, just as I stated below. They're just as plush and soft as ever, with no pilling, pulling, snags or raveling. I've bought more, more than once, for gifts and for my home. An excellent value that I'm glad I took a chance on, first time around.  ORIGINAL POST:  I didn't buy these for anybody's baby, I bought them for me (well, I am somebody's baby, but that's a different conversation). They came nicely packaged, so I would have been satisfied to give them as a gift if I'd bought them for that reason. In shopping around the various baby washcloths, I saw some reviews that mentioned problems with ribbon-tied washcloths snagging when the ribbons were removed. I had no problem with that at all. The package has a seal that specifically states the washcloths should be washed before use, in clear HOT water and dried, to tighten the weave. I did that simply by soaking them in very hot water and then wringing out and hanging up to dry. Afterwards I washed them as I will usually do, with delicate items in a normal wash cycle in cold water with detergent then fabric softener. I think that I read somewhere that softener shouldn't be used on bamboo, but I only use what I can clean without fuss, so... Anyway, so far the washcloths remain soft and no snags after just a few uses. I'm well-satisfied with the quality and the price. I give 4 stars because I want to see how they hold up to repeated use and laundering; so I may post back with an update.

column6: Philips Sonicare Essence Sonic Electric Rechargeable Toothbrush
column14: My dentist thinks I floss daily. This, along with "pro" mouthwash, keeps my gums healthy. This is the lowest cost version of Sonicare. It works as well as the expensive Sonicare. They vibrate at a high frequency, a loud hum. Compare sanding a piece of wood by hand to using a power sander. This is a similar principle. It runs for 2 minutes, so you don't rush through it. The heads need to be removed and rinsed at least weekly, and gelatin from the toothpaste will seep in and gunk it up. The brush works by resonating, and any gunk makes it much less powerful. The test is to wet the brush and turn it on. If the water does not shake off the bristles in a second, the head has a problem. Clean it or replace it. They are expensive, so try soaking overnight in water, then shaking or tapping.

column13: The best sunless tanner I've used
column14: Being about as pale as it's possible to be, I've used lots of sunless tanners. This is by far my favorite. It's tinted, making it easier to see where you're applying it and giving instant gratification. I've found that the color lasts 3 to 4 days, a bit longer if I apply if a few days in a row to make it darker. I was able to use it on my body and on my face with no issues. It provided a nice, natural looking color. It was easy to apply, too. It comes with protective gloves, an application mitt, and a spray bottle of the product. You simply put on the gloves, put the mitt on one hand, spray product onto the mitt, and in a circular motion apply it to your skin. You'll want to exfoliate your skin first for the best results. I find it helpful to lightly moisturize the knees, elbows, ankles, and between the toes. Those areas tend to absorb more of the product and pre-moisturizing them helps keep them from getting too dark. I'll most certainly be purchasing this again and I'm very happy that I'll be able to wear my shorts and swim suit on vacation without looking like a white corpse!

column13: Much better than previous rotary head shavers I've tried
column14:
This was the second of two new razors I purchased. This was considerably more expensive, but does an excellent job. No electric razor I've ever had matches a blade razor and this one is no exception. But I knew that going in. I tried a rotary shaver many years ago and didn't feel it gave a good shave. This one is much better. I use this with a light touch. I think that avoids razor burn. Stretching the skin first helps a lot.

I initially thought I had not gotten a good charge because the razor seems VERY slow. But after recharging there was no speed increase. Still, it seems to cut as well as previous shavers, including the foil types. It also seems to do well with the longer, softer hairs on the neck. With foil razors, I've taken a first cut with the beard trimmer. But this one seems to do the job with just the rotary heads.

column6: Joico Color Balance Shampoo
column13: The blue color is pretty bright and pigmented
column14: This actually works for orange hair, because blue is the opposite on the color wheel to orange so it neutralizes it. The blue color is pretty bright and pigmented. I have balayage highlights ranging from ashy blonde to a warm brown (which is the part that turns orange due to underlying pigmentation since I have previously dyed my hair red and have naturally black hair). The difference between this shampoo and violet shampoo--which I also use--is that the blue neutralizes the darker ORANGE pieces while the violet shampoo only neutralizes YELLOW. However, the violet shampoo will leave yellow pieces brighter while the blue shampoo will kind of dull the yellow pieces and give it more of a gray tone rather than a white tone. Sometimes I like to mix the two shampoos together near my ends, but I concentrate the blue shampoo on the top of my head where the hair is overall darker (and therefore more orange). I usually leave it on for about 3 minutes in the shower and I feel like the blue shampoo is more drying than the violet shampoo, so definitely use a deep conditioner afterwards. It's worth defeating the brass though!

column6: Bamboo Spa Moisture Gloves 1 Pack(s)
column13: so I have to continuallywatch out for outbreaks
column14:
I live with cold-weather eczema on my hands, and since moving to Colorado, it effects me for 3 seasons out of the year, so I have to continually watch out for outbreaks, and prevent them as much as possible, because I make my living using my hands. I'm a writer.

I ordered these online after searching all over town for gloves I could wear overnight to keep moisurizers on my hands. (My kind of eczema results in the skin on my hands not being able to absorb moisture properly. I cannot just rub lotion all over my hands because it won't absorb into the skin; it just leaves a slimy grease all over them, and then I can't use them. If I wipe off the grease, my hands are left dry, cracked, and itchy--and eventually the skin will become thick and the cracks will open up like papercuts, bleed, become infected; and cause my hands to turn red, swell, and burn. They're completely unusable by that point. During Fall, Winter, or Spring, my hands can get this bad in just 2 days, if left untreated.) While the gloves are very soft, I wish they were of a bit thicker material and long enough to cover my wrists, because I have to slather my hands with Cetaphil Moisturizing Cream before puting the gloves on.

Problem is, your gloves--being made of thin fabric--absorb the moisturizer, and get saturated with it. Then, I need to put another pair of gloves on (viny) over them to prevent the saturated gloves from leeching moisturizer all over my bed sheets. Of course, the vinyl gloves deteriorate after contact with moisture, so I can only wear them once.

I wish someone would invent some sort of moisture-protective gloves that are not made out of a thin fabric; but a thicker, flexible plastic that: 1) Won't absorb the moisturizer; 2) Won't leech the moisturizer all over bed sheets; 3) Won't deteriorate after contact with moisture so they can be used over and over; and 4) Will extend beyond the palm to cover the wrists.

America is a country of inventors. We invented the technology that eventually was used in small electronics like cells phones and computers; all so we could send men to the Moon and beyond. But no one knows how to invent a glove that will allow those with Eczema to leave intense moisturizers on their hands overnight to treat it.

By the way, I recently found cotton gloves that are used for the same purpose as your gloves--at my local Dollar Tree Store! I won't be purchasing any more gloves from your company anytime soon.. column14: I have oily skin and just recently suffered from acne breakouts. I didn't understand what was going on so I went to several dermatologists. They couldn't figure out what was wrong because I hadn't changed anything in as far as my eating habits and lifestyle other than joining a gym. They prescribed products containing the go to Benzoic/Salicylic acid. Couldn't really take anything with Benzoic acid since it would make my skin prickly and break into a rash. Salicylic acid on the other hand makes me extremely dry and as a result makes my skin produce much more oil. After a year of on and off acne, I tried to find organic alternative treatments and read something about Witch Hazel so I decided to try a product that had it in the mix. I found this after buying some Bee Friendly products (which are amazing btw) and it works! Doesn't dry my skin out but it does dry out the acne. I tried it on a red patch that was about to rear it's ugly head and it stopped in its tracks and went away in a day!

column13: Light Oil Keeps Fine Hair Under Control Without Weighing it Down.
column14: I had been using Paul Mitchell Super Skinny on my hair after washing and conditioning. It didn't work that well, and felt heavy on my hair. I've seen many good reviews and recommendations about this product so I figured I would give it a try. Let me just say that this IS a good product, but it's definitely not for everyone, including myself.
I'm a teen girl with very fair, oily skin with some redness, as well as acne. I wanted something to help cover up my breakouts and redness while also providing SPF. Turns out that this product is not for us extremely pale girls/those who need coverage/those with oily skin.
It's more like tinted moisturizer than anything. It provides zero coverage. And the lightest shade was way too dark for my skin tone. I also don't recommend this to oily-skin ladies because it'll just make your skin extremely shiny and a little greasy.
I ended up giving it to my cousin who has a darker skin tone/no acne or redness. She also has dry skin, unlike me. She LOVED this stuff. She says it evened up her skin tone and gave it moisture/a little coverage. The SPF is a bonus too.
So if you're like me (fair/acne-prone, oily skin) this product isn't for you. I'm pretty disappointed but got a refund without having to send back the product, so that's good I guess.

column6: Dove Men+Care Control Gel, 7 Ounce
column13: Your hair still feels clean and natural, but this gives you more control
column14:
Even with short hair, styling gel comes in handy at times to keep it from looking all disheveled - especially if I go an extra week without cutting it. In my youth, though, I used styling gels a lot more often because...well...I had a lot more hair. :) This is one of the best that I've tried. It offers additional control while still feeling natural.

It has good hold without feeling sticky at all. Some gels are like super glue in that they make my hands feel incredibly sticky and my hair feel crusty. This gel is nothing like that. It helps add some stiffness and control to my hair without making it feel crusty or even sticky when I run my hands through it, and my hands don't feel sticky after applying it (sure, I still wash my hands, but it's nothing like some other gels). Like I said above, my hair still feels natural.

The smell is muted, too. There is a faint scent to it that is like other gels that I've used, but not as strong. I can only really smell it when I put some on my hands and lift it to my nose - I don't smell it at all after I've applied it. I also like that it doesn't add a bunch of shine to my hair like some other products do.

At (currently) $6 for a 7-ounce tube, I think this stuff is a great value for what you get - assuming that you want a natural look. When I was younger, I liked the extra shine and stiff look of other products. At my age, I like a natural look - and this gel provides it.

column6: Nizoral Anti-Dandruff Shampoo
column14: I waited a while to write a review of this, because truth be told I was expecting to either not work at all or stop working. I've done Neutrogena, Sulfur8, Head and Shoulders (all different types), shampoos with coal in it, tea tree, apple cider vinegar (it worked once!), everything, and nothing's worked. And what's better, since I am black I only wash my hair once a week, and I don't even need to use this that often, so I switch between this and other non-medicated shampoos without issues. I keep waiting for it to not work, but I have been flake free for other a month. For someone who's suffered from dandruff since I was a kid, that's amazing. I love it! column13: I think these are a bit too expensive, but it did brighten my skin and tighten my pores very well
column14:
I saw an advertisement on Facebook to get sample of this mask for $1 so I thought I'd try it. I love good face masks and buy singles all the time, hoping to one day find one that's perfect. This one does deliver on it's promise to brighten my skin and tighten pores- I could tell a noticeable difference in my face when I took it off- my face seemed lighter in color, and brighter, and my pores were about as tight as they ever get. I didn't really find that it reduced fine lines though - so far only the 'at home chemical peels' that I use really deliver strongly on that promise, though some various serums and creams do help.

It comes in a net, and it's loaded with a white cream. The mask itself feels like alginate material, and has precut eyes, nose, and lips. The nose was too long for me, so the upper lip portion just was all out of whack. It took a while for me to adjust it so I could breath and so that I had adequate facial covering. It's to be worn 30 minutes optimally. It is very hydrating, and it rinses easily when time is up.

I do like it. I would not pay $20 each for one, but my budget is tight; others might not take issue with that.

column6: Andalou Naturals Age Defying Hair Thinning Treatment System, 3 Piece Kit
column13: Just thought this should be said...
column14:
I'm giving this product three stars because I haven't been using it long. I read all of the reviews for this product and I think it should be stated that relying solely on ANY shampoo, conditioner, or any hair re growth product for that matter is going to prove as inadequate. Hair loss can be due to any number of things and treating it hair loss needs more than one approach. There is no one cure all for this sort of situation. First, research. If you have access to a computer, do your research. Just because a product is organic does not guarentee that it is going to be "safe" for each individual. Next, a proper diet always goes a long way. Having plenty of veggies and lean proteins in your diet is not only going to improve your hair, it'll improve overall health. Lastly, vitamins. Talk with someone who knows their stuff, a nutritionist or natural pathologist can point you in the right direction.

My actual review for this product is as follows:
I did notice a considerably less amount of hair loss after first use. It made my already fine hair feel soft, light, and smooth. I used all three products included in this kit as directed. On top of using this product I also take a daily dose of a multitude of vitamins, especially biotin, B12, super greens, silica, inositol...to name a few. I message my scalp to stimulate blood flow to my hair follicles for at least 15 minutes a day. I eat a balanced diet and I exercise 4-5 times a week. My battle has been extreme amounts of stress, so this is my routine to counter the stress I undergo.

Overall, I like this product, I greatly feel it's worth the price solely on how it makes my hair feel. I can't say that it does what it states it should do, but that is because I have a entire routine in place to help with my situation.
I hope this helps.

Together, the two potent ingredients have lightened my skintone and freckles (from sun damage), and post-inflammatory hyperpigmentation (dark scars from blemishes) as well as given my skin a "lit from within" glow. I have also noticed that my skin is more resilient, less fragile and any blemishes heal much faster.

I spread 5-6 drops on my entire face, twice a day after cleansing and drying off, then I continue with the rest of my skincare routine. The texture is slightly viscous, which makes it easy to apply. It absorbs very quickly, is not sticky or tacky, and leaves my skin comfortable after use. It has a light odour of bread/yeast, which is not offensive; in fact, I love it! column13: A Crème Lighter Than Whipped Cream With Great Results!
column14:
I received the Derma e Anti-Wrinkle Vitamin A Glycolic Facial Scrub with Vitamins C and E as a gift (see review), and decided to the order the Derma e Anti-Wrinkle A Retinyl Palmitate crème to use with the facial scrub through the Add-On Item Program. A recent advertisement I read that the crème contains Vitamin A which encourages cell renewal, Vitamins D and E, plus Allantoin which is included for an extra-rich moisturizing treatment. The Seller states it helps diminish the appearance of fine lines and wrinkles, leaving skin soft, smooth, and supple.

Based on advertisements it enhances surface cellular renewal to diminish the appearance of age lines, wrinkles with a rich refining crème. When I first opened the jar, I was amazed at how light the crème appeared, once it was applied on my face it absorbed easily without the greasy feeling and appearance. It is labeled that it contains Vitamin A (Retinyl Palmitate) at a potency of 10,000 I.U. per 100 grams, commonly referred to as the "skin vitamin" and best known for its surface cell renewal properties. Its antioxidant Vitamin E, skin-calming Allantoin and Panthenol, as well as nourishing oils gives your skin the beneficial nutrients deep within the skin‚Äôs surface to address the look of skin aging.

After using the cream for a few days, I was disappointed; I did not see any changes to the appearance of my skin. I kept using the product, and after the first week, people started asking me what was I using different on my face. I mentioned I was trying out the Derma e Anti-Wrinkle Facial Scrub and Crème. I started to become amazed at how I could see the anti-aging effect of this product on my face, where I could see some of my age lines diminished, while other lines have become smaller, quite unnoticeable. It has an amazing affect which allows your face to become firmer, which is definitely a great plus, and I do look years younger.

Since I use other facial products, I would be able to state in a month, if this product is responsible for the great differences I have seen in my skin and face. I am not encouraging that both products have to be used together to see the results I have experienced. I personally like to use products in sets, even though I have other facial products that I use on a weekly basis. I believe using the set does enhance your facial regime, and gives you the opportunity to identify if the product is working to enhance your beauty needs. One morning I used another favorite brand facial scrub, applied it evenly to my face, left it on 15 minutes, and then rinsed my face. Thereafter I applied the Derma e Anti-Wrinkle Vitamin A Glycolic Scrub for 15 minutes, then rinsed off my face and was surprised to see how my face felt much cleaner, the appearance of age improved after using this product. I use the Derma e Anti-Wrinkle crème in the morning and night. The Derma e and nourishing oils in this creme delivers beneficial nutrients deep within the skin's surface to address the look of skin aging. column14:
My girlfriend loves this Hanging Organizer!

I didn't know what to get for my girlfriend's upcoming birthday but she (we) definitely needed a makeup storage bag! We have a small single bathroom with three people in the household so there just wasn't enough space.

This case adequately fits all of her cosmetic goodies including blushes, brushes, lip applicators etc. It is soft to the touch and not stiff. It didn't smell either like some nasty factory. The design is even radder in person. I can say without a doubt that I am amazed at how much this case holds.

My girlfriend now puts all of her stuff away in the case after each morning, and it is easily rolled up and stowed behind the medicine cabinet. Now, no matter what I know I can some into a clean bathroom.

Just in looking at this thing (since I don't use it) it seems very utilitarian and looks super cute when folded up. I want to stress the point that this isn't simply a travel cosmetics case! Too cute for just travel!

column6: [Mizon] RETURNING STARFISH CREAM 60ml
column13: Fades Out Dark Spots, Dry Skin Will Need Additional Moisture
column14:
I was skeptical of this stuff, but a friend who works at Dior swears by it. Six months later, I'm a convert. It's tightened everything up, but most importantly (for me), it's evened out the sun damage on my nose. I'm a very pale blond who freckles easily, and this stuff has faded a lot of the years-old freckles until they're barely noticeable. The dark spots I've been trying to cover for years with concealer and foundation are hard to see even WITHOUT makeup, now.
I don't find this cream to be sufficient as a moisturizer, however. I wash my face, use a hydrating serum, wait a bit, use a hydrating/collagen cream, and then just before bed, I put on the Returning Starfish Cream. If I skip one of dehydration products (my skin is very dry), I can tell. The Starfish Cream is wonderful for tightening skin and evening out skin tone, but it's not great as a moisturizer.

column13: Keratin research!!! Thank you! Thank you! Best hair of my liife!
column14: I cannot tell you with words how fantastic this product really is... I know this product has a lot of reviews therefor my review may not seem necessary but I have to tell you that this is the best keratin treatment you'll ever come by. After applying the treatment my hair is extremely soft my curls are almost gone and my hair is just ...did I say SOFT??? And super shiny. If you read the bottle it says you'll wake up with beautiful hair everyday... Well let me tell you that it is absolutely true! I wake up with beautiful beach waves that I can't stop touching... I'm like a teenager on a first date...cannot stop touching my new soft shiny, freeze free hair. Now I can style my hair straight and it'll stay that way no matter how humid and hot the day may be. And if you are wondering... No I did not get paid to post this review nor I am a robot. If you have questions do ask me. I know what it like to blow dry your hair pin straigh just to see it like that until you think about humidity. How I applied the treatment: It is a must that you wash hair with clarifying shampoo at least three times, and please wash it like you are trying to take out a stain from clothes ( delicate clothes though) after that, blow dry hair straigh and then devide hair into three sections.  Take the product and pour about three ounces (for just past shoulder lengh hair) into a container, Then  start by taking very very small sections of hair and then wearing gloves dip three fingers in the product and work it into hair from top to bottom, now use the small thoothed comb and comb the section a few times making sure it's saturated but almost no product it's coming out infront of the comb, if more than half a penny size it's coming out you are applying too much product, do this with the whole head and then blow dry hair using a brush to dry it straigh... This will help tremendously when you start flat ironing. When flat ironing make sure that you take very small sections of hair as this will ensure amazing results, make sure that sections are not more than a quarter inch thick and Definately make sure that they are smaller than the width of your flat iron. Ps make sure you blow our your hair outside of your house an use a fan when flat ironing the hair. Enjoy your new hair.

column6: \Mirenesse Cosmetics\" Secret Weapon 24hr Eye Liner - Purple Rain 4.5g / 0.16oz - AUTHENTIC"
column13: love it! lasts a long time (even if you have oily eyelids)
column14:
I've been really happy with this eyeliner. Liquid eyeliners are my go-to type, since I have oily eyelids. Once liquid eyeliners are set, they don't move for me (whereas pencils, gels, etc., migrate up my eyelids). This one definitely stays in place and doesn't migrate or flake off. It is just as pretty and purple at the end of the day as it is at the beginning.

This does not irritate my eyes (I wear contact lenses and have somewhat sensitive eyes). It is also fairly easy to apply (I have better control with one hand than the other, though). The wand is easy to grip and the brush is fairly thin, giving you the ability to make a thinner or thicker line (by making a second swipe). I am able to remove it with some Acure argan oil cleansing wipes (that just happens to be what I have open at the moment) and think most eye makeup removers would do a similar job.

After you put this on, I'd advise closing your eyes for a moment or two to allow this to dry properly. It works over powder eye shadow and primer particularly well.

Also, for what it's worth, this product is definitely competitively priced on Amazon as of the time of writing this review.

I will NOT be buying Remington ever again, for the rest of time.

0/10.

Henna Maiden come with the henna, gloves, plastic cap and instructions in the package. I added a teaspoon of salt as suggested in the direction for a deeper color and about a cup and a half of hot water. The one packet of Henna Maiden was more than enough for my neck length, fine hair. I left it on for 3 hours under a heating cap. It took about 15 minutes to rinse out with conditioner. After I dried my hair - WOW! It looked thicker, had a little shine and was much smoother and soft to the touch. The color is slightly darker than I expected and darker than the picture online. It's still lovely. Next time, I'll forgo the salt or try the light brown.

I use it for evening and indoors foundation and Garnier BB Skin Renew anti-aging cream for daytime outside wear bc it's  more dewy looking and moisturizing in sunlight.  I am 59 and find that these two combinations of tinted moisturizer work better for me than heavier foundations.  I use light/medium for Garnier w my summer tan but find that level 1 of Paula's Choice is a better shade bc it has brown rather than yellow tones.  Paula's Choice is matte, firming and even toned,  My husband says it looks more like my natural skin.  In high humidity it also holds up extremely well. column14:
I love candles and have them all over my house. Many surround my bathtub, some are in my fireplace, and quite a few are in my bedroom to light up at night. I love their aroma, their ambiance and the romantic vibe they give off. It was only recently that I first heard about wax massage candles and it's many benefits. I bought a small one to test it out and fell in love. Now I don't just have regular candles by my bathtub, but also dedicated massage candles. I really love this one because of it's fantastic spa-like fragrance. Lighting the candle immediately puts me in a state of deep relaxation while the actual wax helps moisturize my skin after my bath. It feels luxurious and reminds me of an expensive spa treatment right in the comfort of my own home (and way cheaper too!).

Just a few tips: make sure you burn the candle for a few hours to get the benefit of the massage wax. You really need plenty of wax to use it as a massage oil (and any left over melted wax just hardens back into the candle anyway). Also make sure you keep the wick short!

column13: Moisturizes and plumps while being great for sensitive skin.
column14:
I will add a disclaimer that I am biased towards the Skinfood Honey line. The Honey Cleansing Cream is the greatest product that I have tried in the last 5 years. The hydrating mask is fantastic. The serum is divine. Basically I want to try out the entire line because it just keeps getting better.

And I love the packaging for everything. Including this eye cream. The print is so cute, and the little gold cap adds a bit of luxury even if this is not a super expensive product.

I also want to mention that 30ML is quite a large size for an eye cream. Mine have always generally been smaller.

But onto the actual product.

It's a slightly yellow tinged cream, the consistency of Cerave in the tub, maybe a bit thicker. No real smell for me. Which is kind of a bummer because I love the way the rest of the line smells. I am not under any sort of misconception about eye creams. I know that they won't cure under eye circles or fat deposits. All I am looking for is some intense extra moisture because I want that area to be as plump as possible. And this provides it on that front. But it could stand to be slightly more moisturizing and thicker. That is a personal preference though. It definitely sinks into the skin quickly.

I also want to add that this feels great on the skin. I have tried too many anti aging eye creams, even expensive ones, that straight up STING when I put them on. And this one does not. Which is lovely.

column6: Hydroxatone Anti-Aging BB (Beauty Balm) Cream, Universal Shade for ALL Skin Types, SPF 40 (BONUS Pack of 2, 1.5 ounce bottles)
column14:
Firstly, let me give an overview of my complexion. I am 24 hrs old, light skin with first signs of fine lines under my eyes and mouth, heredetary dark circles and uneven skintone due to light blenish scarring in the past. I have normal-oily skin. More normal during winter time and oiler during summer time. My Tzone is the first to fet oily after a while. I do not have acne or pimples, although I do get the ocassional pimples during that time of the month. All I was looking for in a BB cream is good coverage to even out my skin tone,cover up my imperfections, lightweight, sunscreen and most importantly, something that would blend with my skin and nit sit on top of it. I have tried a lot of drugstore BB creams, including the Loreal magic Bb cream, garnier bb cream for combo/oily skin, the maybelline stay matte bb cream and some high end ones, the smashbox bb cream, stila cc cream and so on... Obviously, none of those performed how I wanted them to, so here I am.
With that being said, this bb cream does all of the above!!! I picked this up at Costco to try out and was very skeptical about the results, but decided to give it a fair try. I wore this after washing and moisturizing my face and underneath I wore the Lancome Vissionaire 1 minute blur. The moment I put the BB cream on top, the universal shade seemed toooo dark, but after I started to blend, it seemed to work with my skin tone and give it just the right amount of warmth. It blends beautifully, fairly quickly and it sets right away. It melts with your skin and feels and looks like you are not wearing any makeup whatsoever. It has the perfect coverage for what I was looking and it can be buildable. I did set it with a powder which I pretty much always do since I dont want my oily Tzone to come through a few hours later. Accidentally, I fell asleep in my couch that night and moved my way into my bed a few mins later, completely forgetting I had make up on! I wake up the next morning, go to brush my teeth, and what do you know! My face looks amazing, fresh and exactly the way it looked like when I first applied the BB cream! What sorcery is this????
All I can say about this is that it completely outdid itself and its exactly what I was looking for, for the past few months.
I am so happy the package comes with 2 bb creams, so I dont have to repurchase anytime soon and that I have a good backup :)

column6: Banana Boat Baby Sunscreen Tear-Free Sting-Free Broad Spectrum Sun Care Sunscreen Lotion - SPF 50, 8 Ounce
column13: Like the pink and red of the bottle?  Buy this product.
column14:
Unbelievably terrible sunscreen. I live in Hawaii so I frequently go through sunscreen. This is without a doubt the worst sunscreen I have used. Heck, even the bottle looks sunburned. I have gone through the entire tub - because clearly it takes me a while to learn the true value of a product - and every time I have worn it I have come away burned. And it's not like I am putting it on, and then sitting in the sun for 18 hours. I reapply frequently and still burn like I put nothing on. Rather than buying this product, I recommend you go to the grocery store, buy a tub of crisco, and marinate your skin in that before hitting in the sun. How this is considered a product for those with the most vulnerable skin - babies - is beyond me.

I am giving this one star because I think I have to give it at least one star for it to register on the site and because banana boat deserves at least a star for the gall of releasing a product this contrary to what it is advertised as.

Don't buy this product if you want skin protection. Do buy this product if you hate your children and think it's time for them to learn a lesson on the power of the sun.

column6: Magnesium Oil
column13: Has helped with my muscle spasms...
column14:
I'm a member of a Facebook group, Magnesium Advocacy. I know my magnesium levels are low and when I tried taking one form of magnesium, it didn't agree with me very well. I wasn't aware that Magnesium isn't well absorbed by the digestive system. It's much more difficult to absorb if you are low in vitamin D, lack in gut bacteria or have other issues. I am low in Vitamin D and have gut issues. I'd read about Magnesium Oil in this group, that it might be a better option, and had considered trying it. I was given the opportunity to try MAG Essentials Magnesium Oil at a discount for my honest and unbiased opinion. This is my experience so far.

I haven't used it very long, but it HAS made a difference. I've had muscle spasms in the area of my shoulder blade for the past five days. There was no discernible reason, nothing I had done (to the best of my knowledge) to cause this. I've sprayed Magnesium Oil on the affected area and it appears to be helping where muscle relaxants, pain killers, and laying on a heating pad wasn't.

Magnesium Oil has many benefits beyond what it's done for me so far. I highly recommend doing personal research and looking into the Facebook Magnesium Advocacy group I've mentioned. The group has people who are knowledgeable about Magnesium, it's benefits, and they often post research on this subject.

column6: Precious Essentials Oil Jasmine Absolute w/Jojoba Aura Cacia 0.5 oz Oil
column13: Perfect Product for Light Oiling Long Hair!!
column14:
I have been using Aura Cacia Jasmine Absolute for many years, however, I use it differently than what I've read in the reviews.

I actually have very long hair (almost six feet of it) and long hair must be oiled or there will be severe damage. Six feet of hair is over fifteen years old, so the ends are extraordinarily fragile and if not diligently kept, will start to thin with breakage.

Since the carrier oil is jojoba, it is a "top" or light oil, which isn't absorbed as deeply as a "mid" like coconut or "deep", like shea. After washing my hair, I use a bit of shea and jojoba mixed and twice a week, I use the jojoba only (on dry hair) to keep my hair smooth and shiny.

The best thing about this particular brand of oil is that the Jasmine scent is intoxicating! Every time I take my hair down to brush it out and braid it for the night, the room smells like jasmine and I find that I get lots of comments on how pleasant my hair smells!

It's a natural jasmine scent without being perfumy, but rather, smells quite like the Confederate jasmine that grows over my fence!

I've enjoyed telling several of my friends, both white and women of color (those of us with natural hair have to use natural products to maintain length) and it seems to have the same effect on all three hair types (mine is straight with a bit of wave, medium fine but thick) and it's not too heavy for my medium fine hair, for comparison.

So even though I'm not in to aromatherapy or oil burners, I do use this exclusively and frequently and spend pretty much my whole life within a few inches of it and I love it!

column6: ToiletTree Products Bamboo Bathtub Caddy with Extending Sides and Adjustable Book Holder, 4 Ounce
column13: I shouldn't have to \MacGyver\" my bath accessories"
column14: Oh how this had possibilities...wide enough for my garden tub, beautiful bamboo construction, a perfectly appointed place for my phone and wine, and then the book back rest...non adjustable!  I want to read in bath and I read on my iPad.  The back rest tilts back so far that in order to see the screen I practically have to be sitting perfectly high and straight backed, not ideal for a relaxing bath.  Sadly I tossed the packaging into the trash before trying this item or it would have gone back.  It's a great bath caddy with one major flaw :(. I did find a comb that I can wedge behind the book back rest to bring it forward and that works, but for $40 I shouldn't have to "MacGyver" my bath accessories.

column6: BRAUN SERIES 7 799CC-6WD CC4 Wet & Dry Shaver
column14:
I bought the Braun 799CC after using a Norelco SensorTouch 3D 1250x for three years. The Norelco gave a very good shave, actually the best wet/dry electric shave I'd had up to that point, but recently Norelco changed the design of the replacement head and the new head is nowhere near as good. In fact, it's terrible. You can read all about it on Amazon under the RQ12+ and RQ12/52 replacement head model numbers.

Lucky me -- the Braun 799CC is actually much better than the Norelco SensorTouch 3D 1250x, even with the old head. The shave is much closer and my beard grows back more evenly. The cleaning system is better and the travel case is, too. While I'm very disappointed that Norelco made me flush my $220 investment down the drain, in a sense I'm glad they did because I've found a much better shaver in the Braun 799CC. Highly recommended.

column14: I recently tried L'Oreal's [[ASIN:B008EKY8VK Revitalift Triple Power Deep-Acting Moisturizer]] and didn't care for how heavy and sticky-feeling it was. Because this moisturizer was billed as \\\lightweight\\\\\" and because of the 20 SPF (most moisturizers are 15 SPF), I thought I'd give this one a try. It is less heavy than the deep-acting moisturizer, but it was still too heavy for my skin. I wanted to wash it off right away, but resisted. It never really blended in, and it was hot, so I eventually did wash it off. It's a shame... I'd really like some company to come up with a higher SPF in a lighter lotion. I also don't like this pump bottle. Pumps waste so much product and I tried to see if I could pry open the lid, but couldn't. That means there's going to be a lot of waste. The scent is nothing I care for, either. It's kind of like the natural or organic products that try not to be scented, but end up with a kind of industrial smell."

column13: Tried every brand, these are the best, by far
column14:
I've had many eyelash combs through the years, and this model has the best length teeth with the right width in-between the teeth. Yes, you must be careful about pulling too hard as the teeth can be removed---I have had this same model in the past. I bought two combs for just this reason, it is easy to replace the teeth that fall out: remove a tooth from one comb with tweezers, then place it in the emplty hole, unless you are lucky enough to find where the tooth fell.

But...it is easier not to pull the teeth too hard when they are wet with mascara, just lightly rub the teeth against a tissue, better if the tissue has some alcohol on it. I wash them once a week with a soft tooth brush wet with shampoo and baking soda. Rub gently with the brush, pat dry and set out on a towel to dry completely. Great purchase. These were impossible to find in any drugstores, or the Walmart, K-mart, Target type stores, so I was thrilled to find them here. Never ever bother with plastic combs, waste of time and money, much too thick to work.

Do NOT use them on dry lashes, all they will do is pull out your lashes. I put on several coats of mascara, and comb and kind of wiggle the comb through the wet lashes to evenly spread the mascara and remove clumps.

column13: Epsom salt is a natural organic fertilizer
column14: Epsom Salt is a natural organic fertilizer.  Don't invest your hard earned money on "Miracle Gro" or other plant food, Epsom Salt will help your plants to 1) Improve seed germination; 2) increase nutrient absorption; 3) have greener plants.  I've learned that plants which are not getting enough magnesium can be identified by their yellowing leaves. This is because magnesium is an essential component in the production of chlorophyll. Try sprinkling Epsom salt around your plants to achieve healthier foliage. About 1 tablespoon per 12 inches of height once a month will benefit the plants in your vegetable garden, as well as any trees, shrubs, flowers and grasses you want to green up.  It also deters slugs.  For your house plant, I add one tablespoon of epsom salt per gallon of water in EVERY watering session.  This particular Epsom Salt has a "flake like" feel to it, unlike the ones I've brought in the local pharmacy which feels more like small crystal rocks.This type of Salt absorbs very quickly in soil and water and it is genuinely pleasant to handle.

column6: Castor Oil - Jamaican Black - 8 oz - Stimulate Hair Growth
column13: Long-Time Customer of Tropic Isle Living Jamaican Black Castor Oil
column14:
I have been using Tropic Isle Living Jamaican Black Castor Oil for years so I'm excited to have the opportunity to be able to review this awesome product. This is a 8 oz. bottle of Tropic Isle Jamaican Black Castor oil. The bottle is plastic which is nice to prevent breakage. The bottle has a regular screw cap but no dropper or special top to prevent an accident over spillage. I would suggest to use a dropper instead of pouring to prevent a mess.

Jamaican Black Castor oil is light/dark brown color and has a burnt nutty smell. It doesn't smell like regular castor oil so don't be alarmed. Jamaican Black castor oil has that burnt smell and dark color due to the way it's processed. Castor beans are picked and set out to dry to allow the seeds to pop out of their pods. The seeds are then roasted and pounded into mulch. The mulch is then put into a pot with water over a slow wood burning fire. The pot is continuously stirred until the oil rise to the surface and then is skimmed off the top. When the process is completed, all that is left is the ultra pure, light to dark brown, ‚ÄúJamaican black castor oil.‚Äù

I have always used Jamaican Black Castor Oil for my hair, it is great if you have thinning edges. I have made plenty of concoctions with Jamaican Black Castor Oil to slather in my hair as a conditioning treatment and my wild mane of curls is always smooth and soft. You can also use this oil to help with your eyelashes and eyebrows. It's great for tightening pores and cleansing your face, healing blemishes, scars, and rejuvenating the elasticity of your skin. Some people even use JBCO as a pain killer to help with back pain and arthritis.

Bottom line is this product is amazing. I can't say enough good things about it. I have used this brand for years even before writing this review and I will continue to use this brand/product. If you want a good product that can help with your hair, face, and skin this is what you want.

column6: The Bare Pair 'Threesome' King Kombo - Body Hair Management System (w/ Exfoliating Glove)
column13: I just works. Follow directions and advice from fellow reviewers.
column14:
Fan of the Balls! Worked great, as long as you follow the directions and the helpful comments left by other reviewers. I started with a "small" area on one thigh. Put it on, set a 13 min timer, then jumped in the shower and gently scrubbed off. Worked like a charm. Waited 24 hours, did again, to whole legs, hips down. Small issue this time. Just things guys don't think about - the crease of our "bikini area" is sensitive, guys. That one burned for a day. No problem, just put the Calm Balm on it that night, then 3 times the next day, and very little irritation. Red patch stayed for 4 more days, but definitely worked well.

Unfortunately they do not include spreaders anymore, and I have sensitive skin. I have found that using nitrile/latex gloves helps keep my hands from burning, and it helps to spread the cream more evenly.

Additional note to guys who are starting like I did - from full hair. Bring an extra washcloth or 2 with you into the shower. The glove quits after 4 swipes. Again, this is only on the first session. Subsequent sessions have gone much smoother (pun intended).

Now for the part guys want to know about - Balls, Bilson Bridge, and the Butt. YMMV, but I found that it works very well there as long as you limit your times. I found that for my initial application, I chickened out and once there was a tingle at around 8 minutes, I was NOT having what happened to my bikini area happen to the holy places aforementioned. It only removed ~1/3 of the hair. I waited 3 days for a second attempt, left it on for 11 minutes, and viola. Smooth as eggs. The area around the anus is clearly the most difficult, but over the course of 3 applications spaced out over a week, it is 90% smooth. You do not want to be careless in application there. A chemical burn there will make you consider walking into traffic. Go slow, stick to the outside rim, and take your time.

Wrapping this up, great product. Stinks, but not nearly as bad as Nair for Men or Veet. Do your maintenance at night, sleep after you rinse it off, then shower in the morning with soap and smell is barely there.

I have to admit when I received this soap the first thing that stopped me was the size of the jar. It's small; as in 2 ounces. However, after the first use I realize this jar will last for a long time!! A small amount of this thick soap goes a very long way.
When I was my face with this soap, I make sure my face is damp, then I use a little spatula to take the smallest amount out of the jar and I start by massaging the soap around my face. The soap creates excellent suds to remove make up and dirt while the coffee grinds exfoliate.
I've been trying to think of a way to describe the scent of the soap. There is the slightest scent of cocoa right at first, then it becomes a very earthy scent. Personally I love the scent. Once you rinse your face the scent goes away completely.
As soon as you rinse your face you will immediately feel a difference in the texture of your skin. So very soft! SO VERY smooth!!
Added bonus: I've Been Carded has a shelf life of 5 years.
I don't have a single whine. My skin feels amazing! Smooth and soft! I highly recommend Desired Diva I‚Äôve Been Carded Black Facial Wash.

column13: Opinions of a dedicated non-aerosol shave cream user
column14: I started using non-aerosol creams because of the advantages in travelling, and would never switch back.  I have used 3 different non-aerosol shave creams, and consider all 3 good, and all 3 roughly the same price.  Edge has an advantage of being more visible on your face while your shaving in the shower (which I do).  It's disadvantage is that the tube itself is difficult to squeeze when it gets low on product, making it difficult to use all of it.  The others I've used are Gillette Body (amazingly slick, if that's an advantage, but difficult to see on the face) and Neutrogena (which Amazon sells in packages of 2, but has no other disadvantages).  The last one is my preference.

column6: Secret Outlast Clear Gel Antiperspirant and Deodorant Scent, 2.7 Ounce
column13: Nothing Special, but a Decent Product
column14:
As a member of BzzAgent, I received a free sample size of this product to try and review. I have used it for nearly 2 weeks.

PROS:
scent isn't too over-powering
scent if fresh, clean, not too floral
good odor control
washes off easily in shower, leaves no residue
dries quickly once applied

CONS:
leaves some white marks on clothes (despite stating it doesn't)
will not work for 48 hours, that's bogus
need to reapply if you are sweating a lot or it loses efficacy

OVERALL RATING:
Not a bad product, I like that it goes on smoothly and dries fast and isn't a pain to wash off. However, it will still leave white marks on clothes. Not as badly as other deodorants, but they do still exist. I don't think this is the best product for me in the summer months, but in winter it may be adequate. I'm a sweater, so I need a product that will keep body odor at bay.

column6: 36 Pieces Twinkle (NOT Tinkle) Eyebrow Shaver Razor Bikini Trimmer Shaper Sensitive & Delicate Skin
column14: I purchased these before I read the reviews and thought "what the heck...did I make a mistake". I got nervous and felt duped before I even received the box. I read a lot of negative reviews and few positives. That being said, I have had a great experience using this product for the first time. They aren't fancy looking by any means but They do work. One has to remember these are not regular razors...thus you do not hold them to your face or use them as such! You have to pull your skin taught, use small stokes and tilt the razor so it feels and sounds like it is exfoliating the hair and skin. Just because you put it to your face and suddenly stroke downward does not mean it is going to remove the hair. If it is not in the proper angel it will not remove the hair. I recommend watching a tutorial on how to properly use a razor like this on YouTube. If used right it will work. Now, I do pluck a thick hair now and then with tweezers...these razors will shave or exfoliate thick hair off to a certain point. I'd rather not take chances so I pluck the thick ones. The rest I will be using these razors or a product similar to this one when the box runs out. For the price you can't beat the quantity. They aren't meant to last forever so let's be realistic. I'm sure they will last a long while though. It's a good buy for the price and they do work when used correctly. So watch a tutorial. Oh and personally they work best on face and are a bit tricky around the eyebrow if you are trying to angel it near your eye. So I would recommend not using it near your eye in case of an eyebrow mishap. Use a smaller one or pluck the hair. That being said go for it if you are looking for a deal and an exfoliating razor.

column6: Hypo Tears Hypo Tears Hypotears Lubricant Eye Drops, 1 oz (Pack of 2)
column13: Avoid artificial tears that use benzalkonium chloride as a preservative
column14:
Probably no point to posting, as these are no longer available except from ebay or other sellers.
However, for those looking for dry eye relief, beware of these and any other formulation that includes benzalkonium chloride. Testing for decades has determined that benzalkonium chloride actually damages and kills eye cells, yet some manufacturers still use it as a preservative.
While many people may report relief by using this, any long term use is likely damaging to your eyes.
If in doubt, google "dry eye benzalkonium chloride" and then follow the links to the actual medical test results.

I have probably been curing longer than instructed per Gelish, but their lamp has a higher wattage so I'm not sure of the difference, if any.  I just use the 90s timer between each coat to be on the safe side.  I also do my thumbs separately at my own preference because I use them to fix any mistakes and for cleanup, but you should be able to do all 5 fingers at the same time if you choose.  Now I can't wait to get more colors!!

column13: I can't tell you whether this product works or not ...

The product arrived in a sealed box that is identical to the ones skinmedica sells and it had a flier inside on how to enter skinmedica sweepstakes for a free TNS serum which is a current offer from skinmedica.  I weighed my empty bottle and the new one and the new bottle was 1.1 fl oz which compares well with the amt. stated on the bottle and box.  Just my two cents worth...

column6: Sally Hansen Miracle Gel, Pink Tank 0.5 fl oz (14.8 ml) by AB
column14:
This is now my favorite nail polish. I love the color. It is very similar to Sally Hansen's Insta-Dri in Sonic Boom, Sinful Colors in Thimbleberry, and Clinique's A Different Nail Enamel in Hot Pink. I've used this polish several times with the miracle gel clear coat and found that my finger nails lasted about 2 weeks and my toe nails lasted 2 -3 weeks at the beach!! My biggest compliment concerning this product is that it doesn't scratch off on paper that I'm handling at work. I'm attorney so the last thing I need are pink streaks of color across a client's original documents or contracts. I stopped painting my nails for a while because this became a major problem with regular nail polishes that I tried. I've only used this polish with the miracle gel top coat, so I can't attest to how well it will wear without the top coat.

I found the polish easy to apply, and it dries within 1 -2 minutes. You don't need heat or UV light to cure this polish. It dries just like normal nail polish. For bolder color I apply two coats of color followed by one coat of the clear miracle gel top coat polish (black bottle). The end result are shiny, colorful nails that last! This polish is a little pricey, especially if you buy the top coat, but I have been very pleased with it and will definitely buy it again.

column13: two step process for grey hair and blondes going dark! must read!
column14: I buy mine at a store and just came on here for reviews.  I tried this product for the first time yesterday.  I initially got the above pictured box and thankfully called customer service because having some grey hair, I am not supposed to use the regular light mountain.  If you have gray hair, you have to use light mountains COLOR THE GREY line.  If you cannot find color the grey then buy the red henna (has a picture of a Fox on it) and then also buy the color you desire.  First apply the red henna for 15 min to roots where gray hair is or all over if you have gray hair all the way down your length.  Then just rinse and apply henna of the color you want and leave on the necessary time.  This way your gray hair will get a red tint and that will allow it to grasp the next color you put on it.  If you have grays and you only use regular light mountain, which is one application, then your Gray's will either turn blue or green.  You HAVE to use red first on your grays and then the color You want,  if you have gray hair or blonde hair that you are trying to dye dark.  In other words, it's a two step process for people with gray hair or blonde hair who are going dark.  Hope this helps those that ended up with green or blue hair who were either gray or trying to go dark from blonde.

column6: Skin Toner by Ageless La Cure - Natural, Organic Hydrating and Refreshing  with Witch-Hazel Water and Rose Water by Phyto 5, 6.75 Ounce
column14: I know that most dermatologists do not advise that their patients use a toner ... that's fine, I get it. With that said, I still use a toner because I just plain like the way it feels. In fact, there is little I love more than returning from a grueling run, popping out of the shower and then running a cotton pad drenched with toner over my face. It gives me that little extra burst of clean and have a nice cooling sensation (yep, it's alcohol ... I know).  This particular toner is glorious. It has a very subtle rose fragrance and leaves my skin feeling very smooth, very soft, and very supple. I have used this nearly everyday after working out and showering ... and I have had zero negative effects. It did not strip my skin ... at all. (And, I use prescription retinoids every other day, so if it were harsh, my skin would have peeled like crazy). Moreover, I am sensitive/allergic to SO MANY products ... I had no reaction to this toner at all.   For me, this is the first toner that did not interact with my retinoid routine. And, between its gentle but phenomenally effective quality, I am completely sold! (And, the fact that it smells incredible is just a huge plus!) I will absolutely be purchasing this in the future (over and over).  Finally, try this with organic cotton pads ... rather than the traditional, bleached ones. That might make a difference for you.
