column6: Sulfate Free Volumizing Shampoo and Conditioner - Promotes Growth, Enhances Thickening, and Gives Extra Volume to Thin, Fine Hair (8.4oz)
column13: Drying/Damaging Shampoo. Conditioner Is Good. Smells Like Suntan Lotion.
column14: I rarely leave negative reviews, but on this shampoo, I feel compelled. I am giving 2 stars. One for scent, which I do like. Two for the conditioner, which is ok. The scent reminds me of Hawaiian Tropic suntan lotion. I don't find it overpowering. Just a light, fresh, summery scent. I have very fine hair which started thinning about 10 years ago. I am 36.  My once kinky, curly hair now has only a slight wave and frizzes like nobody's business. I went from 3B/C to 2A, for those who are familiar with hair types. It was always fine, but I had a very full head of hair. For whatever reason, my hair texture significantly changed and has never grown back. My docs haven't been able to find a medical cause. My worst areas of thinning are at the crown and sides. My hair parts in the back, which is a double whammy. I struggle to cover my scalp. I also find I have to cleanse my hair near daily. After a day or two, it can look very oily, which makes it look even thinner. I'm sure there are many who can relate to how upsetting and frustrating this can be. Folks like us are always looking for the latest and greatest hair loss treatments. I work very hard to preserve and maintain the health of the hair I have left. I use Ion demi-permanent red hair color (7IR), which I brighten/freshen every 2 weeks with either Manic Panic or Pravana. I am also an avid Wen user. It has done wonders for my hair over the past year. Those products combined help keep my hair shiny, full, and free of split ends/breakage and frizz. All that said, I do use a regular shampoo a few times a month to remove any product residue from my scalp and/or silicone build-up on my hair. The only shampoo(s) that typically touch my hair are Nioxin and Paul Mitchell Tea Tree. Neither of which are particularly ‚Äúred-color‚Äù friendly, but they do help keep my scalp clean and exfoliated and deep clean my hair. I avoid other "shampoos," but this one had so many great reviews, I just had to give it a try. I wish I hadn't. I lost more hair after 3 uses of this shampoo than I have over the past few months. I watched my red color POUR down the drain. It always runs red, but I haven't colored in 6 weeks. I literally cried. With Wen and my regular shampoos, the red doesn't run after this amount of time. This shampoo is sulfate free, so it doesn't have a high lather, but you may find you have to use more product/water than normal to cover your hair. I have used many sulfate-free shampoos. In comparison, this one is sub-par, at best. You will go through a lot of product. When you first apply the shampoo, it has a lot of slip and feels very smooth. Unfortunately, after about 20 seconds, it works like a vacuum; sucking every last bit of moisture out and turning your hair to straw. When I rinsed my hair it felt like a matted mess. I am sorry to say, this shampoo is horrible. If you have hair like mine, or color red, I STRONGLY suggest you steer clear. Now, on to the conditioner. This product was surprisingly pretty good. It is thick and emollient. A little goes a long way. The shampoo seems to significantly rough up your cuticle. I found the conditioner quickly smoothed and detangled my hair. It has the same scent as the shampoo. I air dry my hair. After using these products, my hair looked dry and dull. As nice as the conditioner is, it's not good enough to undo the damage the shampoo causes. My hair looked greasy by the end of the day. I had noticeable hair breakage and visible split ends after 3 uses. Highly UNimpressed. The ingredients listed on the labels are hard to read, but I‚Äôll do my best. SHAMPOO: Water, sodium cocoyl isethionate, cocamidopropylamine oxide, cocamidopropyl hydroxysultaine (Watch this one. It‚Äôs known to cause over-drying and allergic reactions. It‚Äôs synthetic surfactant), disodium laureth sulfosuccinate (While not technically a ‚Äúsulfate,‚Äù it‚Äôs a surfactant works in the same fashion. Common ingredient in most shampoos. Just as an FYI, this stuff is also used in industrial cleaners in higher concentrations.), sodium lauryl sulfoacetate (Not at all environmentally friendly. Toxic to fish and aquatic life.), glycerin, PEG-150 stearate, benzophenone-4 (Known allergen. FDA approved for use in sunscreen. Assuming this provides some protection for the hair.), citric acid, guar hydroxypropyltrimonium chloride, polysorbate 20 (This one is potentially dangerous. Treated with 20 parts ethylene oxide, which is a known carcinogen.), methylchloroisothiazolinone (anti-bacterial/anti-fungal), fragrance, Red 40, Yellow 6, linalool (Not sure on the spelling here. I can‚Äôt read the label. Could be a fragrance). CONDITIONER: Water, cetearyl alcohol (Alcohol, enough said), stearyl alcohol (Again, alcohol), behentrimonium chloride (Known human/environmental toxin.), sodium pca, sodium lactate, arginine, aspartic acid pca, glycine, alanine, serine, valine, proline, threonine, isoleucine, histidine, phenylalanine, hydrolyzed wheat protein (Careful if you have wheat allergies.), hydrolyzed wheat starch, aloe barbadensis juice (aloe leaf), mangifera indica seed butter (mango), theobroma cacao seed butter (cocoa), cetrimonium chloride (topical antiseptic), benzophenone-4, glycerin, phenoxyethanol, benzoic acid (Draw your own conclusions. From the CDC website: The substance irritates the eyes, the skin and the respiratory tract. The substance may cause a non-allergic rash on contact.; The solution in water is a weak acid. Reacts with oxidants.; Dust explosion possible if in powder or granular form, mixed with air.), dehydroacetic acid, fragrance, Red 40, Yellow 6, and again linalool? Overall, thumbs down on the shampoo. Thumbs up on the conditioner. This conditioner may work well for those who need more intense hydration or have thicker/coarser hair they like to co-wash. If you want to risk it, go for it, but my bottles have gone in the trash. These 4-5 star reviews have me baffled. column6: Vanicream Sunscreen Sport, SPF 35 4 oz
column14:
I purchased this sunscreen for my daughter, as an alternative to the typical drug store types that contain endocrine disruptors (Vanicream was recommended by a biochemist colleague who also has a daughter and who indicated it did not). Many of the zinc oxide based sunscreens leave out the estrogenic mimics. I was disappointed to see that Vanicream does contain 2.8% Octinoxate, which is a known endocrine disruptor (perhaps they changed their formula). For detailed information see
http://www.safecosmetics.org/get-the-facts/chemicals-of-concern/octinoxate/
Note in the product description they state Oxybenzone Free. I should have been more attentive to see that it contains Octinoxate instead. I will not purchase this product again. I now buy Blue Lizard.

column6: Jergens Natural Glow Instant Sun Sunless Tanning Mousse
column13: Good self tanner- Best application process below :)
column14:
Jergens sunless tanning products are the tanning trend right now, so I ordered some, and tried them out. The color was not very dark. I used the medium to tan skin tone color, and I didn't really see as much of a difference as I had for. This DOES NOT give you a tan like you see lifeguards have! Only gave me like a shade darker, which isn't much.

FOR BEST APPLICATION:
Use a mitt- BronzeGlow mitt from Ulta works best
Exfoliate before applications- You can exfoliate by buying Jergens shower scrub, or by shaving, or buy using soap and a loofa and scrubbing
Apply lotion before application to dry areas...knees, elbows, knuckles, ankles, etc.
Moisturizer After application- You can buy Jergens tan extender, which is basically just lotion in a fancy bottle, or you can just use lotion
Takes about 6-8 hours to dry-wear loose or no clothing during that drying time
Wash off color guard- after the tan has dried for 6-8 hours take a shower to wash off the colorguard and get rid of some of the self tanner smell
Moisturize- continue to moisturize your body every day to keep your tan for as long as possible

column6: ProNu Anti-Aging 24k Gold Collagen Eye Mask (Pack of 10)
column13: Great for Emergency Days of No Sleep
column14: It took me awhile to figure out how to best use these.  I tried using them without refrigeration, and that did not do much.  I tried putting them in the crisper drawer of the fridge, and that did not do much.  I finally put them directly on the fridge shelf, and that made them nice and cold - very soothing.  Then I tried putting them in the freezer for about two minutes, and they immediately froze and were too frozen when I used them - it stung, but quickly de-thawed.  So, that having been said, I did not notice any difference the first few times I used them, but the truth is I had gotten a good night sleep and did not have a lot of lines, puffiness or bags or dark circles under my eyes.  Then I went through a period when I was intensely involved in a project at work and I was not sleeping - at best getting 5-6 hours of sleep at night no matter what I did - my brain would not shut off.  It was at that point that I noticed new lines developing under my eyes, eye puffiness, dark circles, etc.  You know the routine.  It was at that point that I used these ( I was horrified going to work looking so awful - the eyes are where it shows), and I immediately noticed a huge difference in the appearance of my under eye area.  The horrible wrinkles that had started to form were less visible.  The area looked brighter.  The puffiness gone.  SO, that having been said, I don't know if these work wonders when you don't really need them, but for those nights of no sleep, put these in the fridge for 5 minutes, use these in the morning (I do about 1 hour if I have the time) and it will improve the appearance of fine lines and puffiness under your eyes.

column6: Manly Guy Hair, Eyebrow, Beard, & Mustache Color: 100% Natural & Chemical Free
column14: UPDATE: For those who mentioned their hair turning orange: This happened to me, at first, particularly where my facial hair is pure white (the top part of my mustache and my goatee). The solutions that worked for me were to leave the product in longer or to re-apply later. The packaging doesn't lie. First-time users should leave it in as long as they can. The packaging recommends up to three hours on your first try. Tedious? Yes. But it works. After the first time, when your hair has a "head start" on the dye, then you can leave it in for less time.  I tried this at a friend's suggestion because I developed a sudden, violent, painful allergy to that OTHER product and I was assured that, not only was Manly Guy non-toxic and chemical-free, but that the color would look more natural and the product wouldn't stain my skin.  I'm happy on all three counts. This is a GREAT product. My beard & mustache look terrific after using it.  PROS: 1. Easy to use: It's just powdered henna mixed with warm water. I don't have a thick beard, so I ended up needing much less than the instructions recommended. I mixed three tablespoons' worth, and I really only needed 1.5, but no big deal. Even though the instructions say not to, I did use an applicator brush from that OTHER product to work the mixture into my beard, then followed that up with a healthy dollop from my fingers to get complete coverage. You'll want the mixture to be thick, like pancake batter, not runny. 2. Doesn't stain: This was one of my biggest worries. That OTHER product would stain my skin no matter how hard I tried to keep it from spreading there. Manly Guy washes right off, even if it sits on your skin for a while; although I do recommend you wear gloves when using your fingers to apply the stuff, simply because it's messy. (You're going to go through a lot of paper towels.) 3. Great color: My natural hair color is light brown, but as I've gotten older, my facial hair has gone almost completely white. This stuff did a great job of covering that up. The package recommends that first-time users leave it in for 1.5 to three(!) hours. Because I was in a hurry, I only left it in for an hour, and I still got great results. My facial hair is now light brown with just a little white poking through to give me a salt & pepper look, which I actually prefer. NOTE: You will very likely see a tinge of green in your hair when you first rinse the product out of it. This is temporary. Within an hour or two, the green will fade away and you will see the color you're supposed to see. 4. No chemical burns or blistering: Pretty much says it. Went on and came off without any pain, discomfort, or disfigurement. If you have sensitive skin or allergies, then you should consider trying it.  CONS: 1. It takes time: You need to allow enough time for the product to work. As I said previously, I left it in for an hour, and I think that's the least amount of time where it would still be effective. If you have thicker hair, then you'll probably need to leave it in even longer. Also, remember what I said above about the greenish tinge. It will likely happen to you, but it will go away on its own. Just remember that it can take a few hours. If you can, put it on a couple of hours before bed and, by the time you wake up, it will be a normal color.  2. Moisture: It only works as long as it's wet, so you can't let it dry out. My friend recommended that I wrap my face in plastic wrap, but I found that really awkward, so I just misted my face with a spray bottle every few minutes. Either way, you're in for a little tedium. Wear a t-shirt that you don't mind getting dirty, because some of the product is going to end up running down the front of it. 3. The smell: The smell isn't *bad*, it's just... well... earthy. It's like dead grass or algae mixed with dirt. Not the worst thing I've smelled, but not what I want to walk around smelling like, either. The instructions say you can add a little scented beard oilto the mixture, if you like, so I'll try that next time. 4. Messy: Since you have to mix the product yourself, there's plenty of potential for messes. Also, as I said above, you're inevitably going to get some of the stuff down the front of you, so plan accordingly. I just wore an old tank top that I wouldn't miss if it were unrecoverable. (The product washed right out of it, incidentally.)  All of that said, it's a great solution if you have the time and you FOLLOW THE INSTRUCTIONS. It's a good alternative to that OTHER product, especially if, like me, it suddenly started setting your face on fire.

So for me, I can't use it on my face but it's a great for removing dead skin from my body instead. This will be part of my weekly body exfoliation rotation now.

column6: Bare Minerals Make Up
column14:
I've been using this product for years--ever since it first came out in those sample size kits. As a person with sensitive skin, finding anything that doesn't cause some kind of irritation or breakout whether it be cosmetics, lotions or soaps has been a lifelong challenge. When I first purchased the kit I thought it was a modest enough investment to determine if it would be a good choice for my situation.
What a wonderful surprise to find something that goes on quickly, easily and washes off with simple soap and water. It does cover well using a small amount of product and the brushes blend it all in without all those telltale lines. You don't have to constantly fuss over it or freshen it like some of the others. It covers well presuming you have an average skin condition. Severe scars or other marks may be beyond the scope of the product. It evens out skin tones and the mineral veil finishes it all off. It is an age neutral product--in other words women young and mature can use this without looking overly 'made up' if that is the goal.
There have since been other manufacturers that have taken up the trend if you will, of mineral cosmetics, but this line, especially the mineral veil still stands out. Perhaps it is that slightly pink hue that brings a more flattering glow to the skin without looking like something pasted on. On a final note, if your skin tends to be dry, a bit of light moisturizer to start may be helpful in the application as it is a loose powder. Enjoy!

column6: Burt's Bees Basic Face Care Kit
column13: I have a crush on this set.
column14:
I have a crush on this set. I usually buy things that promise to reduce my pores, reduce effects of aging, brighten my skin, blah, blah, blah. I sometimes forget that my face needs relaxation, good moisturizing, and a clean slate. I really like the wipes, and I have already purchased more of these. The face wash is gentle but effective, it has a creamy texture, you mix with water, you don't get suds, you just get a thinner cream that spreads evenly on your face. There is a slight medicinal smell to the cleanser and it provides your face with a fresh tingly feeling. I like how fresh and clean my face feels after washing up. The moisturizer is divine for my face. You know how some days the regular wear and tear of the day has your skin just begging for a drink and bedtime...enter this thick creamy moisturizer, light scent if any, it spreads on easy - a little goes a long way - and it soothes the day away. I had been out at an event near a very windy body of water, my face felt wind burned, sand scratched, and just tired. I washed up and reached for the nicest moisturizer in my arsenal, this was it. In the morning my face looked plumped back up to health and ready for a new day.

I like the wipes for a variety of reasons, but if you use other masks, or perhaps you need a refresh, but not a full on face wash, these come in handy. I used them frequently. And all of these products were less expensive than what I had been using on my face, and have a better reputation for being ecological and kind.

column6: Yes To Carrots Intense Repair Daily Hand Cream, 3 Ounce
column14:
This hand cream was not an "intense repair" as described -- it is more the consistency of a body lotion than hand cream. I was also disappointed by the scent, since I was expecting the delightful scent of the Yes to Carrots body butter, but this is very lightly scented and not nearly as nice of a smell. I will use this up but not purchase again.

For comparison, Gardener's Hand Creams are thicker and work better than most of the other natural hand creams, such as Burt's Bees Ultimate Care Hand Cream, Collective Well-Being Hand Cream, and Desert Essence Organics Pumpkin Hand Repair Cream (the latter of which is worthwhile just because of its delicious pumpkin-spice smell!). All of these work better than this Yes to Carrots hand cream.

Burt's Bees makes a Beeswax Almond Milk hand cream that has more natural ingredients, and smells so delicious, but is leaves hands feeling greasy, and fingerprints on everything touched after using it. I've tried several of the JR Watkins Hand Creams and Hand Repair Balms by Upper Canada and find these to have superior moisturizing, with much nicer scents than this Yes to Carrots hand cream.
(yes, I realize that I have tried many, many hand creams, but hopefully comments about all of my purchases allow you to better select one for your needs)

column6: Miss Jessie's Quick Curls
column13: This is my curly hair go-to cream -- love it!
column14: I'm caucasian and love using this cream on my hair on days that I want to go curly or wavy. I used to describe my hair as naturally curly, but now its more like naturally wavy. If I let it dry on its own, I don't get ringlet curls -- just a lot of volume and frizzy hair. I usually wear my hair straight because its easy to dry mostly straight with a big round brush and blowdryer. However, in the summer especially, its nice to have to the option to do something different without too much frizz from all the humidity (I live in the south). I found that this cream is very lightweight, so it doesn't weigh down my hair, but it does an amazing job of controlling frizz. I even use it sometimes when I blow-dry it straight just for frizz control. If I use this for curly days, I apply the cream allover my hair. Then I separate my hair into smaller sections and re-apply to each section, twist each section away from my face, and then let it dry. When the section are mostly dry, I shake them out for soft and gentle ringlets. This is the only product I have found that works for me. Also, it smells really good. I recommend giving this product a try.

Highly efficient roll-on. Pleasant smell though we (the editorial "we") would have liked more smell of patchouli than this batch gave off. Our goal was to remind everybody in a not too subtle way that we were believers in the "hippie thang" way back when and still like to rock.
That said, the stuff smells clean and good. Wears good through a 15 hour day and multiple airports. "It keeps the stank off ya!" ....and that's why we wear deodorant. Figure about 7 months of use with a pack of 6 roll-ons. Only recommendation we have to the folks who make it? "Lay that patchouli on thick enough so that when's we walk by....people will turn and say ,"I remember the day" and smile. column13: It smells awful, but it works!
column14:
I have keratosis pilaris and have been trying to find a solution for years. I had tried countless moisturizing products and exfoliation products. I even tried Korea Italy towels after reading so many great things about them from others with KP - nothing groundbreaking. After about 3-4 days of using AmLactin, the results were drastic. This is the FIRST product I have found that actually works on my condition. This is the first time in my life since the age of 12 that my arms and legs are silky smooth.

It's worth noting that the smell of this product is not attractive. It isn't losing a star for smelling like ammonia since that is one of the active ingredients, and clearly it works.

It is not a miracle cure, but it is effective treatment for extremely dry and bumpy skin. After using this consistently for 1-2 weeks, I enjoyed the benefits for another 1-2 weeks before I really had to reapply.

column6: Caswell-Massey - Sandalwood Cologne Spray
column14: Once upon a time there was a scent called Piping Rock -- it was about the driest, cleanest sandalwood scent ever. This stuff is a bit sweeter and spicier, but not all that different. The first resinous, turpentine-y blast smells like a sawmill, and as the scent continues it reminds me a bit of other sandalwood classics -- Habit Rouge, the aforementioned Piping Rock, Jade East (but in a charming way), and at the end good old soap.  This is a great scent for summer evenings, because it doesn't disappear in a flash. I recommend walking through a few sprays of this after a shower. But a word of warning -- there really are benzene ring compounds in there, and this stuff can stain a white shirt like crazy.  Don't worry. That warm, clean tropical scent will drive women nuts.

column6: Revlon ColorStay Liquid Makeup for Combination/Oily
column13: I may never use a different foundation after this . :D
column14:
I purchased the Caramel shade of this foundation.

I must say before ordering I was a bit scared to do so because the picture for the caramel bottle advertised is WAY darker than it actually is and I may have never order this if I didn't look at some swatches on google. Than could also be an issue of computer monitors. So, to help you out I posted some pictures, with and without flash of the product in the bottle and a tiny bit on my finger and how it blended out on the palm of my hand. When it dried I rubbed one of my fingers on it with much more force than needed and NO SMEARING AT ALL. A+++++++

I am a previous Black Opal user in the shade Truly Topaz and upon visiting a department store for a new foundation fix I was told that it was not good for acne prone skin which I do have and needed a change fast. I decided to turn to this because of friends of course. We went to a party and it stayed on all night long for her so I quickly went to this one.
I tested my shade on findation.com by putting in previous foundations I've used before and this shade fit me PERFECTLY. A few other foundation have been a bit to yellow or light for my skin but this one was great. I also experienced little or no oxidation.

It was easy to apply. I use makeup sponges. Always better to use damp makeup sponges if you want lighter coverage. It is a bit tricky using your fingers but not suggested because it may be hard to blend out as it dries so quickly and after that, the damage is done. It can also be veryy messyyy. Which would make a pump very useful... which i wish i wish with all my heart I could have gotten, though I could just transfer it to an airless one ounce pump bottle. Those are fairly cheap and its worth it avoiding the mess of application. It never settled into fine lines and never creases. Like it sits on your face but you don't feel it? Like its not sticky or anything. So hard to describe but whatever it is, it's great.

The longest I have tested it for with my E.L.F. makeup primer is 9 hours and my skin (normally very oily skin) was in the same condition as my skin would be in 1-1.5hrs of using my Black Opal. Practically still fresh. So when hey say 24 hours, it may not quite be 24hours but pretty damn close!

One thing I noticed when I opened it was the faint smell of paint but nothing strong enough to scare me away. The smell fades a while after it dries on my face. Maybe say... 30mins?
Overall, I would recommend this always.est I have tested it for with my E.L.F. makeup primer is 9 hours and my skin (normally very oily skin) was in the same condition as my skin would be in 1-1.5hrs of using my Black Opal. Practically still fresh. So when hey say 24 hours, it may not quite be 24hours but pretty damn close!

One thing I noticed when I opened it was the faint smell of paint but nothing strong enough to scare me away. The smell fades a while after it dries on my face. Maybe say... 30mins?
Overall, I would recommend this always.

column6: Mineral Effects Loose Mineral Makeup Medium Tan
column14:
I actually purchased this for myself and find that I don't care enough about wearing makeup to take the time to put it on.

However, my husband, who has Lupus (which is almost completely gone) has a couple of spots at the temple area and is extremely self conscious of it.

He, being the troubleshooter (and the good fortune to be an excellent artist), immediately saw the potential in this makeup and using sable brushes, is able to perfectly blend it into his natural skin (he only uses it on those two spots) and it's almost invisible.

You'd have to be looking for it to know it was there and I'm going to go out on a limb and say that it doesn't enhance wrinkles, because he's sixty years old!

So, I'm assuming it's a great foundation powder (even for aging..aged? skin) and it also hides blemishes in about a second and a half!

column6: J.cat Beauty Eternal Shine Lip Gloss Set - Set of 36 Shades with Aloe Vera and Vitamin E
column14: For the shear amount of different colors you get, I really can't complain about the price. However, this is still somewhat different than I expected.  I guess these are smaller tubes than i thought they would be - although the size is clearly listed in the description.  At a glance, I do like the majority of the colors as they are in the tube. There are some colors that are just weird to me, but those could look great on someone else. To note- some colors are very very similar - even when put right next to each other the difference is minimal - i don't know if you could tell the difference when on.  I have only tried about three different colors. On me, the color looks much lighter than it does in the tube. The application instrument is the foam brush, where I would prefer a different applicator (the kind that resembles the nail polish brush- I don't know the name of this).  I will say this gloss does feel a bit tacky/sticky when put on.  And you do really need to reapply frequently.  I would say if you just had this on and did not drink/eat anything etc.. it would maybe look fine for an hour (that is being somewhat generous).  With that said, for the price, you can afford to reapply.  I can't really say I'm thrilled with this purchase, but I'm not super disappointed either.  This did arrive quickly and was packaged well - this is a side note but when I opened these my immediate thought went to that these would be fantastic to divide up and give as little gifts with some other girly stuff to female friends or family members.

column6: Gillette Venus Bikini Kit
column14:
The bikini works fine if you want an EXTREMELY SHORT trim. Easy enough to maneuver, though a more narrow model would be a tad easier to navigate through tricky areas. Personally, the trim was far too short for me, and left hair at a length that was just scratchy and painful for a week until it grew a bit.

The "bikini lotion" is just Oil of Olay's regular intensive moisture lotion repackaged. Nothing special. Did not prevent razor burn, and was a bit greasy.

The razor gave me a very nice shave on all parts, though the moisturizer does get goopy and will leave residue on whatever you set it down. It also dries in a funky shape. So, leave it sitting blade up and flat.

column6: Reusable Premium Cosmetic Makeup Sponge Egg Drop Applicator Smooth Puff Foundation Blender for Beauty by JGOB
column13: Best makeup product I own.  Saves money on expensive foundation!  Love it!
column14:
My Dolce Peach Applicator Makeup Blender Sponge has changed my opinions about sponges. I have used a few and found I wasted a ton of makeup in my sponge and stopped using them. Then they would be so hard to clean as they were all soaked in foundation. The cheaper sponges were streaky and could not be used easily around my nose unless i squeezed into a smaller shape. Then as you probably know the absorbed foundation comes out of the cheap sponge like a glob in the creases of your nose when you squeeze it to fit in tight areas. The JGOB sponge has stopped all that! It's amazing! I just put in water, squeeze it out and add a touch of foundation. It keeps the foundation where it should be on the outside of the sponge, not inside. It is shaped perfectly in a teardrop shape so you can get the hard to reach smaller areas and the larger areas. It spreads so easily and evenly. The best part I am no longer wasting my expensive foundation by letting it get washed down the drain with my old sponges. The JGOB sponge cleans up easily and you will see there is hardly any makeup left in the sponge after using. It comes with its own travel case and it keeps it clean in your makeup bag. It is perfect for older skin, that tends to get easily flaky and streaky. This applicator is does not increase flakiness since it does not take multiple attempts or fussing on your skin for application to achieve evenness. Best makeup product I own and I will save money on foundation!
**I received this product free or deeply discounted for a honest, unbiased review. My opinions are my own.

column13: One of the Best Beauty Bargains
column14:
This is a lightweight, non-sticky moisturizer, with no added fragrance.

What it does have are ceramides, hyuralonic (however it's spelled) acid, niacinamides, and some nice antioxidant and anti-irritant ingredients at a fantastic price. It helps maintain even skin tone, and contains ingredients that are good for skin, even and especially sensitive skin.

But you don't have to have sensitive skin to appreciate a quality, affordable nighttime moisturizer. And if you have oily skin, you simply must try this. It's not going to clear up zits, but it won't clog your pores, and it doesn't feel the least bit greasy. It won't spread over to your hair at night, either.

In fact, if anyone hasn't tried CeraVe PM, what's the hold up? A skin care product that won't harm your skin is a must try, in an ocean of skin care products with dubious ingredients. Two wings up!

column6: ULTIMATE OCEAN Mineral Hydration Creme Anti Aging Facial Moisturizer, 90+ Ocean Minerals, Blue Green Algae + Irish Moss + Hyaluronic Acid Will Repair, Rejuvenate, Deeply Hydrate Your Skin!
column14:
I have been using 4 of the Azure Naturals products so I am going to review in order of recommended use.

The seaweed hydration mask is really cool. It is not clay based so it doesn't get super stiff like some of the masks I have used in the past. The hardening of the masks really bugs me as I am not a big fan of putting things on my face, but also know I need to take better care of my skin. I like this mask because it sort of feels like your skin is tightening but then it can be rinsed off. Like other masks, you use a warm towel to remove it. It is pretty easy to remove it because of the lack of hardening to the face. A lot less messy! My skin feels really refreshed after using it so that is a huge plus!! It smells sort of aloe-y and you don't need a whole ton of the product to get a good spread. It states that it can be used on the neck and whole body as well. I have major sensory issues so I haven't attempted beyond my face :-D but I imagine your skin would feel very refreshing after rinsing it off!

After the mask you can use the cleanser. Sometimes I have skipped this step as my skin already feels pretty good after the mask. The cleanser is a sort of gel and comes out in a pump bottle. It has a sort of smell like a light flower. It dries on your face nicely but if you have any sort of sensory issues, this may be the one that takes the longest to get used to. I only need one pump, lather it with a bit of warm water, and it seems to be enough to cover the face with a frothy thin layer. After you rinse and your face dries it feels nice and seems to leave a tightening feeling on the skin.

The toner feels really good on the face! It comes in a spray bottle and should be used after washing your face and if you have the complex cleanser you can use it after that. It comes out as a beautiful mist that sprayed at a distance, covers my entire face. But I use two sprays just because it feels pretty darn refreshing. It dries really quickly so if you are using the hydration creme, you only need to wait a few seconds to put it on. It smells really good too!

After the toner, and as the final step in the complete series, you use the creme. I love the creme and this is probably my favorite of the four. After all of the work on your skin and face, the creme feels so incredible and refreshing. Again, you don't need a whole lot of it to feel like you have covered your face. It has a really good smell, similar to the mask but not too strong. This is the product that seems to pull it all together for me. When I put it on, it feels like I am sort of giving my skin a protective moist layer to keep all of the good stuff on long enough for my skin to absorb the ingredients. It dries nice and smooth and doesn't feel oily afterwords. I give it some time to do it's job while I change or eat breakfast and then I come back to put some powder makeup on over it.

These products are organic and show you right on the front of the bottle exactly what you are getting, organic aloe, irish moss, shea butter, rosehip, tea tree oil, sprirulina, and sea kelp. Can't get more natural than that! I have all 4 products and using them all together feels even better so if possible, I'd recommend getting one of their toners, cleansers, cremes, and masks.if you are using the hydration creme, you only need to wait a few seconds to put it on. It smells really good too!

After the toner, and as the final step in the complete series, you use the creme. I love the creme and this is probably my favorite of the four. After all of the work on your skin and face, the creme feels so incredible and refreshing. Again, you don't need a whole lot of it to feel like you have covered your face. It has a really good smell, similar to the mask but not too strong. This is the product that seems to pull it all together for me. When I put it on, it feels like I am sort of giving my skin a protective moist layer to keep all of the good stuff on long enough for my skin to absorb the ingredients. It dries nice and smooth and doesn't feel oily afterwords. I give it some time to do it's job while I change or eat breakfast and then I come back to put some powder makeup on over it.

These products are organic and show you right on the front of the bottle exactly what you are getting, organic aloe, irish moss, shea butter, rosehip, tea tree oil, sprirulina, and sea kelp. Can't get more natural than that! I have all 4 products and using them all together feels even better so if possible, I'd recommend getting one of their toners, cleansers, cremes, and masks.

column13: One smooth shave that won't nick you face or wallet
column14:
I really have not experienced what the more negative reviews reflect. I think this multi-blade system just has it all over the big name US brands and the price is so much better. The blades position in the handle does take a bit of getting used to but once you are comfortable finding your grip, the razor just flat out gets it done. Since I have a full beard I primary use a razor to keep my neck and cheeks clean. The King is fabulous at cutting in precise clean lines that are nearly as good as a professional men's barber with a straight edge could do.

If you want a super clean shave with this razor you do need to be aware of "the grain" of your growth in the different parts of your face and go against and not with the grain. Unlike my double edge I need less preparation of the skin prior to shaving and far less risk of nicking myself. If you look at this product price when compared to similar offers from the Big Two in addition to its outperforming them IMHO, you can'y go wrong.

column6: Men's Rogaine Foam One Month Supply
column14:
For anyone who is thinking of using this, I have almost 2 years of experience with it and can give you the honest truth. If you are concerned with your balding and thinning hair, Rogaine can give you an added boost, an offset of growth, that occurs and improves over time, sometimes after a horrible initial shed, the 'dread shed'. When I first started using I lost so much hair, it was raining down, my hair where I applied it looked WORSE than it ever had before. Sometimes I wanted to give it up, but I stuck it out, and I'm glad I did.

Over the course of the first year it was a rollercoaster ride but I had patience and continued the routine, btw with not only Rogaine but other generics too; they all work the same, it's just a matter of taste (or smell) and $. For the vast majority, me included, the shed hairs will grow back, get stronger and thicker over time, and additional new or dormant stimulated hairs will fill in the blanks. Let it be noted that I saw very little to no results for 6 to 8 months, and it got worse before it got better. But eventually all of a sudden what seemed like thousands of tiny new hairs began to sprout in my hairline and throughout my beard, eyebrows and upper cheeks, and with continued application I have been able to maintain and nurture this new growth. At this point, I am considered a hirsute man, which is what I strive to be; No one would know that I'm thinning at all.

There are other things I do to encourage hair growth, Rogaine is only one tool in the arsenal:

Eat a healthy diet. I am vegan, eat tons of fruits and veggies, and a decent amount of soy, which may reduce DHT. I eat organic when I can.
Get regular exercise. I lift and bike and play tennis; get the blood pumping. Go outside, get some sun.
Use Nizoral shampoo once a week, or less; for me it's very strong, and over-use irritates my scalp.
Use a regular shampoo without any weird chemicals, like Dr. Bronners or something natural.
Take a multi-vitamin, I like Alive whole food.

If you decide to, you can take Propecia. Personally I do not, I refuse to risk my sexual health, but I also fully expect to go bald one day and when I do, I will embrace it. But there's nothing wrong with trying to buy a few years with Rogaine ;-) Studies show you can maintain above baseline for up to 16 years with Minoxidil, and possibly beyond that; everyone will respond differently, some probably not at all, but this isn't some snake oil, it absolutely works and will give you more and better hair, at least it does for me.

Also, for any tanner, wearing latex gloves keep your hands clean, and it seems like product applies faster and easier.

column14:
I purchased this product a few months ago when it contained ferulic acid. Initially, the ferulic acid made my skin very red and I thought I wouldn't be able to tolerate it. A representative from the company recommended waiting a few months then trying the product again as they were changing their formula. My skin quickly adjusted to the ferulic acid in the first bottle and I loved it so much I reordered it.

I noticed this second bottle however does not have ferulic acid listed as an ingredient so the company did indeed change the formula. This new product is thicker, unpleasantly sticky and has a greenish-yellow cast that makes me think it has oxidized already although I just opened it. column6: ULTIMATE Seaweed Hydration Facial Mask, 90+ powerful Ocean Minerals, Seaweed, Irish Moss, Spirulina & MSM Will Deliver a Hydration Tsunami to Repair, Rejuvenate & Nourish Your Skin!
column13: Doesn't tighten like a clay mask!
column14:
I have been using 4 of the Azure Naturals products so I am going to review in order of recommended use.

The seaweed hydration mask is really cool. It is not clay based so it doesn't get super stiff like some of the masks I have used in the past. The hardening of the masks really bugs me as I am not a big fan of putting things on my face, but also know I need to take better care of my skin. I like this mask because it sort of feels like your skin is tightening but then it can be rinsed off. Like other masks, you use a warm towel to remove it. It is pretty easy to remove it because of the lack of hardening to the face. A lot less messy! My skin feels really refreshed after using it so that is a huge plus!! It smells sort of aloe-y and you don't need a whole ton of the product to get a good spread. It states that it can be used on the neck and whole body as well. I have major sensory issues so I haven't attempted beyond my face :-D but I imagine your skin would feel very refreshing after rinsing it off!

After the mask you can use the cleanser. Sometimes I have skipped this step as my skin already feels pretty good after the mask. The cleanser is a sort of gel and comes out in a pump bottle. It has a sort of smell like a light flower. It dries on your face nicely but if you have any sort of sensory issues, this may be the one that takes the longest to get used to. I only need one pump, lather it with a bit of warm water, and it seems to be enough to cover the face with a frothy thin layer. After you rinse and your face dries it feels nice and seems to leave a tightening feeling on the skin.

The toner feels really good on the face! It comes in a spray bottle and should be used after washing your face and if you have the complex cleanser you can use it after that. It comes out as a beautiful mist that sprayed at a distance, covers my entire face. But I use two sprays just because it feels pretty darn refreshing. It dries really quickly so if you are using the hydration creme, you only need to wait a few seconds to put it on. It smells really good too!

After the toner, and as the final step in the complete series, you use the creme. I love the creme and this is probably my favorite of the four. After all of the work on your skin and face, the creme feels so incredible and refreshing. Again, you don't need a whole lot of it to feel like you have covered your face. It has a really good smell, similar to the mask but not too strong. This is the product that seems to pull it all together for me. When I put it on, it feels like I am sort of giving my skin a protective moist layer to keep all of the good stuff on long enough for my skin to absorb the ingredients. It dries nice and smooth and doesn't feel oily afterwords. I give it some time to do it's job while I change or eat breakfast and then I come back to put some powder makeup on over it.

These products are organic and show you right on the front of the bottle exactly what you are getting, organic aloe, irish moss, shea butter, rosehip, tea tree oil, sprirulina, and sea kelp. Can't get more natural than that! I have all 4 products and using them all together feels even better so if possible, I'd recommend getting one of their toners, cleansers, cremes, and masks.if you are using the hydration creme, you only need to wait a few seconds to put it on. It smells really good too!

After the toner, and as the final step in the complete series, you use the creme. I love the creme and this is probably my favorite of the four. column13: Easy to use, highly effective‚Äîmy hair looks gorgeous!
column14:
As my hair stylist moved & I'm insanely picky about who touches my hair, this was my first time doing my own Keratin Smoothing/Brazillian Blowout treatment.

Upon learning the Chi Enviro treatment appeared to be off the market, I decided on this one based on the positive reviews. Let me say this: those positive reviews are so warranted!

Directions are simple & having been through & watched my stylist do this on my hair for years, I found the application to be easy. Note: even though it's easy, it IS time consuming. Plan accordingly!

I left it in from Friday morning until Monday morning. My first wash, I was expecting to see obvious curl & this has my hair straighter than any treatment used in the past. It's cut my styling time and I can also let it air dry without seeing an awful, frizzy mess. I am absolutely sold on this Keratin treatment. My hair is soft, silky & the time saved is priceless.

Note: definitely use a fan and make sure your area has great venilation. I did & had no problems with lingering fumes, but I can see how it could easily be an issue depending on the layout of your space. I didn't find the fumes insufferable, but there were a couple times where they definitely made themselves known.

column6: QIANSE \Spring of Versailles\" Handcrafted Enamel Butterfly Jewelry Set"
column14:
Having received the Butterfly bangle that matches this necklace and earring set and which I absolutely adore, I was interested to see how this set compared. They match beautifully and the quality is the same HOWEVER a little too big and bulky for my personal taste. (Yes, the bangle is heavy too but sitting on my wrist, I don't notice it as much.)

The earrings are the stud design with a straight post to insert in your ear but instead of a separate back, there is a hinged piece that comes up from the bottom of the earring sitting in place over the post once you have the earring on. I have small holes and could NOT get these earrings on. ( I have not had trouble with any of the other earrings from this company.) The posts are seriously not that big so know that it is the holes in my ears that are the issue.

Two of the butterflies on the earrings and three on the necklace are inlaid with clear crystals. The base color is white but the actual butterflies are a variety of colors, more pastels in shade than bright colors.

The earrings measure nearly an inch from top to bottom and 5/8" wide. The necklace is approximately 1 1/2" high, 1 1/4" wide with a 19" chain. Whilst my own personal opinion is that the bangle is totally modern, the necklace and earrings (to me) have a "dated" feel to them. I, personally, will not be wearing them. Some others are likely to absolutely love them.

That is one of the joys of reviewing as it hopefully helps you, the consumer, make an informed choice. Is this a quality set? Absolutely! It is presented in a nice gift box and would make a lovely gift for someone who likes this kind of jewelry. Keep in mind that this is fashion jewelry. It is only gold plated and not solid gold which the price reflects.

Product provided in exchange for an honest review. Thanks, Liz

column6: 18k Gold and Rhodium Plated Sterling Silver Two Tone Diamond Hoop Earrings (1/10cttw, I-J Color, I2-I3 Clarity)
column14:
These are pretty earrings, but up close, there are some things that don't show up in the listing image.

First, it looks like a row of diamond chips, when in fact is is a row of silver dots with a diamond added in here and there. They are not sparkly like I would expect from diamonds, since there are only 5 chips on each earring.

Second, the quality of the gold plating isn't flawless. I will add a photo to the review that shows where there is a dark flaw in the gold. There are several of these spots that look like a smudge or something.

Third, they are smaller than I thought. they fit on my pinky, if that helps for a size gauge. The inside diameter is a half inch and the diameter of the full thickness is 3/4 inch.

Finally, the posts are thicker than my normal earrings, so they hurt my ears. The first time I wore them, it was a bit of a struggle to put the in, and I wear earrings every day. I have not yet been able to make it through a day before removing them because my ears hurt. I think it is because of the size of the post, but I can't be sure it isn't the material.

These come in an attractive black box with no brand on it. It has just a "Made in China" sticker on the bottom. There is no paperwork certifying the materials they are made of. I'm not likely to purchase something from this collection again. I like to have some sort of paperwork or certification that tells me what I bought. The stamp on the gold, read with a magnifying glass, says PA 1925 China. It doesn't say anything about gold.

They do have a nice design, in that the detail on the front is carried to the inside of the back so when you are wearing them, they look richer. But design isn't everything.

While I love the way the ring looks, it is a little too thick to be comfortable to wear on a daily basis. As such I wear this ring only for special occasions where I do not have to do a lot with my hands (such as going out on the town at night or for a special dinner date). I find it too thick to wear to work for example where I have to type, handle books, papers, etc.

Still a beautiful ring that is elegant and fancy!

column13: Perfect Pendant and Earring Set for Every \Kitten Loving\" Little Girl or Young Woman!"
column14:
If you have a Little Girl or Young Woman in your life who is a Big Fan of Kittens, then this Pendant and Earring Set by SmitCo LLC is sure to make them Smile!
It Features a 3/4" Sparkling, Crystal Covered "Kitty Wearing A Crown" Pendant complete with Silver Tone Whiskers.
The Too Cute Pendant is strung onto a 17" Silver Tone Ball Chain with a Lobster Claw Clasp by way of a Silver Tone Bale and is accompanied by a Pair of Matching 1/2" Crystal Covered "Kitty Wearing a Crown" Earrings.
The Crown on the Pendant features 6 - 1/8" Pretty Pink Crystals, while the Face features 29 - 1/8" Rhinestone Crystals, along with 2- 1/16" Black Crystal Eyes. The Back of the Pendant is a Textured Solid Silver Tone Alloy Metal.
Each of the Matching Earrings feature 6- 1/16" Pink Crystals in the Crown, 30 - 1/16" Rhinestone Crystals in the Face, 2 - 1/16" Black Crystal Eyes and have Textured Solid Silver Tone Alloy Backsides as well.
The Earrings are held securely in place with 1/4" Silver Tone Earring Backs.
All Crystals are Multi-Faceted to Sparkle Like Real Diamonds and Securely Set into the Alloy Metal backing.
This "Kitty Wearing A Crown" Set arrives in a Very Nice Gift Box so there is no need for purchasing wrapping paper unless you so desire.
I received my Set in exchange for my unbiased review and can honestly say that this Jewelry Set will Not Disappoint even the most devoted Kitten Lover!
It's a High Quality Jewelry Set at an Extremely Affordable Price and I am giving it a Well Deserved 5 Star Rating!

column14:
This review is for the earrings with the green stones.

In case you were wondering, the posts on these are right in the middle (important in deciding how they will look before purchasing). I have a metal sensitivity so I coated the posts with a few coats of clear nail polish before wearing and I was able to keep them in all day without any trouble.

I love the bright, big green stones. These are nice enough and sparkly enough that you could wear them to an event, but I wore them to the office and they worked in that context, as well. The product photo is an accurate representation of what you receive.

These come in cute little gift boxes. They have some nice sparkle and all the stones (there are a lot of clear CZ stones around the edge as well as the large green stones in the middle) are securely fastened in place. These earrings are quite pretty and reasonably lightweight, which makes them perfect for me.

Product provided by the seller for evaluation purposes.

column6: The Sea of Jewels - Sterling Silver 'Baullarum' Earrings
column14: I was excited to receive these earrings.  They are absolutely beautiful!  They are extremely well made and shine as brilliant as a real diamond.  They are set in real settings as well, not like those cheap settings where you can tell they are fakes.  I have included a photo to demonstrate the brilliance and size of these earrings, they are very large, the approx size of center stone is 2 carats.  In the photo I am comparing it with a dime and a real 1 carat diamond center stone ring.  These earrings are actually larger than I expected.  I prefer smaller stones as I have small lobes and I really wish they were smaller in size.  I received these earrings at a reduced cost in exchange for my honest and unbiased review,  I am really sad and upset that they are too large for me and I will have to either return them or find someone with larger lobes that could enjoy them.  This review is not meant to deter you from purchasing these earrings, they are stunning!  I just need to advise you that they are quite large for us petite girls, unless you really like big bold earrings, as I assume some of you do.

column14:
This pair of earrings is not one of those that you pick up because you liked the product photo on Amazon and then find disappointingly small or low quality. They are lightweight but not thin or cheap feeling, they have a very attractive knot design, and they're big enough to be a statement.

The way that the silver is turned in the design gives them an unexpected flash when you are out in the sunshine. The color is clear and bright, and they don't tarnish quickly like a lot of my older silver earrings do. I have gotten quite a few compliments on these - I think they're just flashy enough to be attractive without scaring anyone off.

I found the earwires comfortable, but I dislike fishhook styles generally because they tend to drop out of the ear on random occasions. It's fairly simple to replace them with leverbacks, so that's what I did.

column13: Wish I would have gotten this from the beginning!
column14: After closing my hand in the door and cracking my expensive diamond wedding band, I said "screw it" and am opting for an inexpensive, basic, traditional band. My husband got a titanium band from day 1 and has loved it for the 5 yrs we've been married, so I order 2mm & 3mm titanium bands then tried 2mm & 3mm tungstan bands as well. Without knowing which metal was which hubby & I both preferred the 3mm titanium. It's a classic look, super lightweight, and at this price if I do end up damaging it somehow (as I seem prone to) I'm only out ~$10!

Sterling Silver Oxidized Cubic Zirconia Celtic Knot Hinged Bangle Bracelet, 7.25\"	Jewelry	3	1	1	Y	N	Nice Knot, but lackluster stones don't add value to the otherwise nice design	Although I'm not a big jewelry wearer (except for earrings), I confess a weakness for Sterling Silver, which is why I chose this bracelet that boasts a classy looking Celtic Knot design with small Cubic Zirconia stones. For the price (which, in fairness, I did not pay because I received this item from Amazon Vine program in exchange for a review), I expected, at a minimum, a bit of sparkle. The Celtic Knot design looks exactly as in the advertised image, but the stones lack even the tiniest amount of sparkle. I liked the design of the clasp, which is easy to open and close (though I have smallish wrists so I don't need to use it), but the two sides of the knot that contain the stones simply look like indentations on the silver and not like raised stones. The cross-section of the "wire" of the bracelet is a square, which seems like a step up from the standard circular shape, but that feature isn't noticeable except from super close up. In summary, the promised Cubic Zirconia stones add zero sparkle or value to the otherwise nicely-designed knot.	2015-08-09

Sterling Silver Oxidized Marcasite and Garnet Colored Glass Textured Teardrop Pendant Necklace, 18\" Jewelry 5 1 2 Y N Rich Looking and Lovely Pendant + Update This is a really lovely pendant. I have the set and received the earrings first, before the pendant, and since receiving it, I truly love them more.

The design is rich-looking and it is well made. The 18 inch chain is dainty, yet strong enough to hold this good-sized pendant. It's not really heavy, or too large. I have heavier murano glass pendants that are just slightly larger so this is a comfortable pendant to wear. It was easy to put on as well, unlike some tiny spring-ring clasps. I wish that they would use a lobster claw clasp though, especially at this price point. They are much easier to work with especially if you don't have someone handy to help.

I'm including some pictures so you can see the set together. The teardrops are all the same size. At first I thought the earrings were slightly smaller but they are the same. The pendant just has an extra drop link.

This looks great with a red and black print outfit that I have. It sets it off perfectly!

Update- Although I really liked this set, I didn't have as many opportunities to wear it and my daughter liked it more. It looks so good on her that it's now in her collection. These earrings will 'bling without the bling" The classic black minimal style adds just enough accent to your ears without looking comical like some of the other styles I've seen around town. column6: Surgical Steel Nose Stud - Heart
column14:
I bought this for my daughter and I'll admit I am not an expert on nose studs, but here was the issue we encountered. She has a left nostril piercing and when she put this in the heart was upside down. When she tried to straighten out the heart then the end was visible (basically hanging out of her nostril.)

I have jewelry pliers so (with much effort/experimentation) I was able to straighten out the "screw" part and then reshape it so the hook went up into the nostril instead of hanging down.

Maybe it would have been fine in a right nostril...like I said I don't know enough about these things. Just be aware if you are buying for a left nostril you may encounter the same problem we did.

I have to say the stud is very well-made as the steel was quite hard to bend - and even with all my messing around with it the heart stayed attached to the post.

column14: I bought this product as a gift to my girlfriend and as I don't completely trust online products I decided to open it before presenting it to her. Turns out the chain had this giant knot in the middle of it which took me a good 20 minutes to undo. Part of the reason why it took so long is because of how delicate the chain is. I didnt want to damage or break the chain in the process of undoing the knot. When buying a product this expensive I expect the seller to handle it with care, especially when they have 'JEWELRY' in their name. So I hope you understand my disappointment when they throw in a necklace with knots in it and expect the buyer to untie it. I'm very lucky I didnt damage it in the process. Otherwise the product itself is fine.  Might consider using a different chain though.

column6: White Bronze Clear Cubic-Zirconia Earrings
column14:
The design is beautiful! Nice for nightclubbing.
The cubic-zirconia is of a low quality grade; it doesn't have a good sparkle. I don't know what "white bronze" is supposed to be or look like, so I will just describe what it looks like to me: chrome plating.
Love the length - it's 2 inches long. At its widest point (where the post is) it's 1/2 inch across. The bottom cz is 5/16 inch across.
The posts are the standard 11mm length and have double locking notches. These earrings are heavy, and I would recommend using the disc-pad type of earring backs to prevent them from drooping forward.
Overall, these earrings have their good points and bad points, but I can see how they could easily become favorites because of its really nice style.

column6: 8mm Black High Polish Tungsten Carbide Men's Wedding Band Ring in Comfort Fit and Matte Finish Sizes 5 to 16
column13: We bought this ring because it looked very solid and he liked the finish
column14:
I bought this ring for my husband after his original wedding band broke twice. He works in the marine environment outdoors and his original ring quickly scratched and broke apart. We bought this ring because it looked very solid and he liked the finish. After over a year of wear and tear, the ring looks as good as the day we received it. It has a comfort fit band so it is not uncomfortable for him to wear. Here are some pros and cons of this ring for you to make an informed decision.

Pros:
Looks great
Great scratch resistant finish
Hypoallergenic

Cons:
Heavier than some other rings (compared to the tungsten/ceramic original ring)
The raised center band takes some getting used to as it feels larger

I would purchase this ring again if he ever loses it and have recommended it to friends. I think it looks as good as or better than many higher priced rings. If you are looking for a men's ring that can handle some abuse you have found the right ring.

column6: 8MM Black High Polish / Matte Finish Men's Tungsten Beveled Ring Wedding Band
column13: Order ring with expectations that vary ring to individual ring.
column14:
ORDERED:
8MM Black High Polish / Matte Finish Men's Tungsten Beveled Ring Wedding Band Sz 8.0
Sold by: Metal Factory
REORDERED (needed diff size):
8MM Black High Polish / Matte Finish Men's Tungsten Beveled Ring Wedding Band Sz 7.5
Sold by: Metal Factory

I ordered an 8MM Black Polish / Matte Finish ring - I rear a size 8 but the 8 I ordered was too big and would easily slide off.
When I realised that I needed to exchange the size 8 for a 7.5, the ring was unavailable & there was no expected return time. :(

Off-hand I was looking on Amazon for something else on a later date and checked on the ring; it was back for sale. I began the return process for the size 8 and after that ordered a size 7.5.
On the inside of the size 8 was printed the word, 'TUNGSTEN'. Not a big deal, but the 7.5 I ordered did not have TUNGSTEN on the inside.
***Quite probably manufactured by a different company.

Something that did almost immediately become apparent, were the scratches that showed up on the ring's matte surface!
I wore the size 8 two to three times and it remained perfect and untouched. The size 7.5 on the other hand seems to scratch ridiculously easily!
I wore the 7.5 for the first time on a visit with family. Did not touch anything other than food, washing hands, and a few other non-scratching objects. I was looking at it, admiring it, later in the day when I noticed several light surface scratches.

I had read several reviews that proudly exclaimed the scratch-proof/resistant surface--a big reason why this particular ring was purchased in the first place--and now I realise that those observations/qualities very much change with each individual ring.

column6: BERRICLE Sterling Silver 0.74 ct.tw Round Cubic Zirconia CZ Halo Engagement Wedding Bridal Ring Set
column14: Being super pregnant over the summer has been a little bit of a struggle. My baby is due mid August so needless to say, I've been my largest during the hottest months and the swelling is REAL! My poor feet and hands balloon up & sometimes stay that way for hours, causing my real wedding rings to get jammed on my fingers and feeling like they're cutting off circulation! That's where this purchase comes in. I bought these rings as a stand in & even though they're a little smaller than my real rings, they fit wonderfully and have saved my sanity! I don't want to walk around without my rings; I feel naked without them!! But being 8-9 months pregnant, I was bond to need them surgically cut off! So in the meantime, these rings have been a life saver and I've gotten several compliments on them from people who couldn't tell that they are not real. They are starting to fade and tarnish a little but I've also been very hard on them and treating them as if they are real.

column14:
This silicone wedding ring is going to be a big stress relief for me this winter. My husband loses his wedding ring multiple times a winter. I have shoveled snow into a kid pool and melted it in a bathtub to find it when it fell off in the road while getting in the car. It has fallen in a huge container of packing peanuts while packing parts to ship for work. And bounced across many floors. This silicone ring is true to size and comfortable to wear. I love that when my husbands hands shrink it the winter this ring has a little grip to it being that it is silicone so it will stay on, and if it is lost it is easily replaceable.
I received this item at a discount in exchange for my unbiased review.

column6: Moon Wings Solid Sterling Silver Lion Vintage Mens Ring
column14: Little more pricey than what I spend on my rings. I lose them a lot because a lot of the rings I like are skulls and things of that nature. "Biker rings" which only tend to come rarely in size 7 if I'm lucky or bigger.  I refuse to wear tape around my rings and the sizers don't work.  Not the ones I've used anyway.  So I don't usually pay this much for this type of ring. BUT it is so worth it.  It's not all big and bulky. It's beautifully made; gorgeous details. The photos here do it no justice.  The king of the jungle indeed is perfectly portrayed here along with the beautiful tree and giraffes;  and opposite is the most beautiful heart and wings. The craftsmanship and details are beautiful! When I have more than 4% battery I'll upload pics.  Just FYI sizing seems to run a little big ... I was lucky that they made a 7 and it fits loosely on my middle finger.  So I suggest ordering a size down on this one. I Love this ring so much; i will definitely be returning to purchase more items in the future from Moon Wings!

column6: Eove 8mm Tungsten Wedding Band 0.05 Carat Cubic Zircon and Celtic Dragon Blue Inlay Beveled Edges Comfort Fit
column14:
This is a really beautiful ring. I love how it fits. The inside of the ring is rounded, so it slips off and on easily. It is such a comfortable ring. Because it is wide, it is a good idea to purchase a half or full size larger. My wedding band is a size 10 and I received a size 11. The fit is perfect.

The blue engraving around the band is subtle. If you like the look of the single small stone, then rotate it around to the top. On the other hand, if you'd rather a more elegant look, rotate that portion to the inside of your hand, and you have a blue and silver band.

I really love how this band feels on my hand. It is just the right weight; a little heavy so I know it‚Äôs there, but not so heavy and big that it looks ostentatious. Everything about this ring is beautifully finished. The price is perfect - exactly what jewelry should cost.

Presentation is elegant and simple. The ring comes in a brown card stock box. Inside there is a velvet bag. This is simple environmentally responsible packaging.

A free sample was provided for review.
